559 ----
560 static SDValue performDivRemCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
561 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
562 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
563 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps()) 0
564 return SDValue(); 0
565 ----
566 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0); 0
567 unsigned LO = (Ty == MVT::i32) ? Mips::LO0 : Mips::LO0_64; 0
568 unsigned HI = (Ty == MVT::i32) ? Mips::HI0 : Mips::HI0_64; 0
569 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SDIVREM ? MipsISD::DivRem16 : 0
570 MipsISD::DivRemU16; 0
571 SDLoc DL(N); 0
572 ----
573 SDValue DivRem = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, MVT::Glue, 0
574 N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1)); 0
575 SDValue InChain = DAG.getEntryNode(); 0
576 SDValue InGlue = DivRem; 0
577 ----
578 // insert MFLO ----
579 if (N->hasAnyUseOfValue(0)) { 0
580 SDValue CopyFromLo = DAG.getCopyFromReg(InChain, DL, LO, Ty, 0
581 InGlue); ----
582 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), CopyFromLo); 0
583 InChain = CopyFromLo.getValue(1); 0
584 InGlue = CopyFromLo.getValue(2); 0
585 } ----
586 ----
587 // insert MFHI ----
588 if (N->hasAnyUseOfValue(1)) { 0
589 SDValue CopyFromHi = DAG.getCopyFromReg(InChain, DL, 0
590 HI, Ty, InGlue); ----
591 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), CopyFromHi); 0
592 } ----
593 ----
594 return SDValue(); 0
595 } 0
596 ----
597 static Mips::CondCode condCodeToFCC(ISD::CondCode CC) { 0
598 switch (CC) { 0
599 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown fp condition code!"); 0
600 case ISD::SETEQ: 0
601 case ISD::SETOEQ: return Mips::FCOND_OEQ; 0
602 case ISD::SETUNE: return Mips::FCOND_UNE; 0
603 case ISD::SETLT: 0
604 case ISD::SETOLT: return Mips::FCOND_OLT; 0
605 case ISD::SETGT: 0
606 case ISD::SETOGT: return Mips::FCOND_OGT; 0
607 case ISD::SETLE: 0
608 case ISD::SETOLE: return Mips::FCOND_OLE; 0
609 case ISD::SETGE: 0
610 case ISD::SETOGE: return Mips::FCOND_OGE; 0
611 case ISD::SETULT: return Mips::FCOND_ULT; 0
612 case ISD::SETULE: return Mips::FCOND_ULE; 0
613 case ISD::SETUGT: return Mips::FCOND_UGT; 0
614 case ISD::SETUGE: return Mips::FCOND_UGE; 0
615 case ISD::SETUO: return Mips::FCOND_UN; 0
616 case ISD::SETO: return Mips::FCOND_OR; 0
617 case ISD::SETNE: 0
618 case ISD::SETONE: return Mips::FCOND_ONE; 0
619 case ISD::SETUEQ: return Mips::FCOND_UEQ; 0
620 } ----
621 } ----
622 ----
623 /// This function returns true if the floating point conditional branches and ----
624 /// conditional moves which use condition code CC should be inverted. ----
625 static bool invertFPCondCodeUser(Mips::CondCode CC) { 0
626 if (CC >= Mips::FCOND_F && CC <= Mips::FCOND_NGT) 0
627 return false; 0
628 ----
629 assert((CC >= Mips::FCOND_T && CC <= Mips::FCOND_GT) && 0
630 "Illegal Condition Code"); ----
631 ----
632 return true; 0
633 } ----
634 ----
635 // Creates and returns an FPCmp node from a setcc node. ----
636 // Returns Op if setcc is not a floating point comparison. ----
637 static SDValue createFPCmp(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDValue &Op) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
638 // must be a SETCC node ----
639 if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC) 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
640 return Op; 0
641 ----
642 SDValue LHS = Op.getOperand(0); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
643 ----
644 if (!LHS.getValueType().isFloatingPoint()) 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
645 return Op; 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
646 ----
647 SDValue RHS = Op.getOperand(1); 0
648 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
649 ----
650 // Assume the 3rd operand is a CondCodeSDNode. Add code to check the type of ----
651 // node if necessary. ----
652 ISD::CondCode CC = cast(Op.getOperand(2))->get(); 0
653 ----
654 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::FPCmp, DL, MVT::Glue, LHS, RHS, 0
655 DAG.getConstant(condCodeToFCC(CC), DL, MVT::i32)); 0
656 } 0
657 ----
658 // Creates and returns a CMovFPT/F node. ----
659 static SDValue createCMovFP(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Cond, SDValue True, 0
660 SDValue False, const SDLoc &DL) { ----
661 ConstantSDNode *CC = cast(Cond.getOperand(2)); 0
662 bool invert = invertFPCondCodeUser((Mips::CondCode)CC->getSExtValue()); 0
663 SDValue FCC0 = DAG.getRegister(Mips::FCC0, MVT::i32); 0
664 ----
665 return DAG.getNode((invert ? MipsISD::CMovFP_F : MipsISD::CMovFP_T), DL, 0
666 True.getValueType(), True, FCC0, False, Cond); 0
667 } ----
668 ----
669 static SDValue performSELECTCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
670 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
671 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
672 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps()) 0
673 return SDValue(); 0
674 ----
675 SDValue SetCC = N->getOperand(0); 0
676 ----
677 if ((SetCC.getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC) || 0
678 !SetCC.getOperand(0).getValueType().isInteger()) 0
679 return SDValue(); 0
680 ----
681 SDValue False = N->getOperand(2); 0
682 EVT FalseTy = False.getValueType(); 0
683 ----
684 if (!FalseTy.isInteger()) 0
685 return SDValue(); 0
686 ----
687 ConstantSDNode *FalseC = dyn_cast(False); 0
688 ----
689 // If the RHS (False) is 0, we swap the order of the operands ----
690 // of ISD::SELECT (obviously also inverting the condition) so that we can ----
691 // take advantage of conditional moves using the $0 register. ----
692 // Example: ----
693 // return (a != 0) ? x : 0; ----
694 // load $reg, x ----
695 // movz $reg, $0, a ----
696 if (!FalseC) 0
697 return SDValue(); 0
698 ----
699 const SDLoc DL(N); 0
700 ----
701 if (!FalseC->getZExtValue()) { 0
702 ISD::CondCode CC = cast(SetCC.getOperand(2))->get(); 0
703 SDValue True = N->getOperand(1); 0
704 ----
705 SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(DL, SetCC.getValueType(), SetCC.getOperand(0), 0
706 SetCC.getOperand(1), 0
707 ISD::getSetCCInverse(CC, SetCC.getValueType())); ----
708 ----
709 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, FalseTy, SetCC, False, True); 0
710 } ----
711 ----
712 // If both operands are integer constants there's a possibility that we ----
713 // can do some interesting optimizations. ----
714 SDValue True = N->getOperand(1); 0
715 ConstantSDNode *TrueC = dyn_cast(True); 0
716 ----
717 if (!TrueC || !True.getValueType().isInteger()) 0
718 return SDValue(); 0
719 ----
720 // We'll also ignore MVT::i64 operands as this optimizations proves ----
721 // to be ineffective because of the required sign extensions as the result ----
722 // of a SETCC operator is always MVT::i32 for non-vector types. ----
723 if (True.getValueType() == MVT::i64) 0
724 return SDValue(); 0
725 ----
726 int64_t Diff = TrueC->getSExtValue() - FalseC->getSExtValue(); 0
727 ----
728 // 1) (a < x) ? y : y-1 ----
729 // slti $reg1, a, x ----
730 // addiu $reg2, $reg1, y-1 ----
731 if (Diff == 1) 0
732 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, SetCC.getValueType(), SetCC, False); 0
733 ----
734 // 2) (a < x) ? y-1 : y ----
735 // slti $reg1, a, x ----
736 // xor $reg1, $reg1, 1 ----
737 // addiu $reg2, $reg1, y-1 ----
738 if (Diff == -1) { 0
739 ISD::CondCode CC = cast(SetCC.getOperand(2))->get(); 0
740 SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(DL, SetCC.getValueType(), SetCC.getOperand(0), 0
741 SetCC.getOperand(1), 0
742 ISD::getSetCCInverse(CC, SetCC.getValueType())); ----
743 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, SetCC.getValueType(), SetCC, True); 0
744 } ----
745 ----
746 // Could not optimize. ----
747 return SDValue(); 0
748 } 0
749 ----
750 static SDValue performCMovFPCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
751 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
752 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
753 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps()) 0
754 return SDValue(); 0
755 ----
756 SDValue ValueIfTrue = N->getOperand(0), ValueIfFalse = N->getOperand(2); 0
757 ----
758 ConstantSDNode *FalseC = dyn_cast(ValueIfFalse); 0
759 if (!FalseC || FalseC->getZExtValue()) 0
760 return SDValue(); 0
761 ----
762 // Since RHS (False) is 0, we swap the order of the True/False operands ----
763 // (obviously also inverting the condition) so that we can ----
764 // take advantage of conditional moves using the $0 register. ----
765 // Example: ----
766 // return (a != 0) ? x : 0; ----
767 // load $reg, x ----
768 // movz $reg, $0, a ----
769 unsigned Opc = (N->getOpcode() == MipsISD::CMovFP_T) ? MipsISD::CMovFP_F : 0
770 MipsISD::CMovFP_T; 0
771 ----
772 SDValue FCC = N->getOperand(1), Glue = N->getOperand(3); 0
773 return DAG.getNode(Opc, SDLoc(N), ValueIfFalse.getValueType(), 0
774 ValueIfFalse, FCC, ValueIfTrue, Glue); 0
775 } ----
776 ----
777 static SDValue performANDCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
778 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
779 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
780 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() || !Subtarget.hasExtractInsert()) 0
781 return SDValue(); 0
782 ----
783 SDValue FirstOperand = N->getOperand(0); 0
784 unsigned FirstOperandOpc = FirstOperand.getOpcode(); 0
785 SDValue Mask = N->getOperand(1); 0
786 EVT ValTy = N->getValueType(0); 0
787 SDLoc DL(N); 0
788 ----
789 uint64_t Pos = 0; 0
790 unsigned SMPos, SMSize; ----
791 ConstantSDNode *CN; ----
792 SDValue NewOperand; 0
793 unsigned Opc; ----
794 ----
795 // Op's second operand must be a shifted mask. ----
796 if (!(CN = dyn_cast(Mask)) || 0
797 !isShiftedMask_64(CN->getZExtValue(), SMPos, SMSize)) 0
798 return SDValue(); 0
799 ----
800 if (FirstOperandOpc == ISD::SRA || FirstOperandOpc == ISD::SRL) { 0
801 // Pattern match EXT. ----
802 // $dst = and ((sra or srl) $src , pos), (2**size - 1) ----
803 // => ext $dst, $src, pos, size ----
804 ----
805 // The second operand of the shift must be an immediate. ----
806 if (!(CN = dyn_cast(FirstOperand.getOperand(1)))) 0
807 return SDValue(); 0
808 ----
809 Pos = CN->getZExtValue(); 0
810 ----
811 // Return if the shifted mask does not start at bit 0 or the sum of its size ----
812 // and Pos exceeds the word's size. ----
813 if (SMPos != 0 || Pos + SMSize > ValTy.getSizeInBits()) 0
814 return SDValue(); 0
815 ----
816 Opc = MipsISD::Ext; 0
817 NewOperand = FirstOperand.getOperand(0); 0
818 } else if (FirstOperandOpc == ISD::SHL && Subtarget.hasCnMips()) { 0
819 // Pattern match CINS. ----
820 // $dst = and (shl $src , pos), mask ----
821 // => cins $dst, $src, pos, size ----
822 // mask is a shifted mask with consecutive 1's, pos = shift amount, ----
823 // size = population count. ----
824 ----
825 // The second operand of the shift must be an immediate. ----
826 if (!(CN = dyn_cast(FirstOperand.getOperand(1)))) 0
827 return SDValue(); 0
828 ----
829 Pos = CN->getZExtValue(); 0
830 ----
831 if (SMPos != Pos || Pos >= ValTy.getSizeInBits() || SMSize >= 32 || 0
832 Pos + SMSize > ValTy.getSizeInBits()) 0
833 return SDValue(); 0
834 ----
835 NewOperand = FirstOperand.getOperand(0); 0
836 // SMSize is 'location' (position) in this case, not size. ----
837 SMSize--; 0
838 Opc = MipsISD::CIns; 0
839 } else { ----
840 // Pattern match EXT. ----
841 // $dst = and $src, (2**size - 1) , if size > 16 ----
842 // => ext $dst, $src, pos, size , pos = 0 ----
843 ----
844 // If the mask is <= 0xffff, andi can be used instead. ----
845 if (CN->getZExtValue() <= 0xffff) 0
846 return SDValue(); 0
847 ----
848 // Return if the mask doesn't start at position 0. ----
849 if (SMPos) 0
850 return SDValue(); 0
851 ----
852 Opc = MipsISD::Ext; 0
853 NewOperand = FirstOperand; 0
854 } ----
855 return DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, ValTy, NewOperand, 0
856 DAG.getConstant(Pos, DL, MVT::i32), 0
857 DAG.getConstant(SMSize, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
858 } 0
859 ----
860 static SDValue performORCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
861 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
862 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
863 // Pattern match INS. ----
864 // $dst = or (and $src1 , mask0), (and (shl $src, pos), mask1), ----
865 // where mask1 = (2**size - 1) << pos, mask0 = ~mask1 ----
866 // => ins $dst, $src, size, pos, $src1 ----
867 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() || !Subtarget.hasExtractInsert()) 0
868 return SDValue(); 0
869 ----
870 SDValue And0 = N->getOperand(0), And1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
871 unsigned SMPos0, SMSize0, SMPos1, SMSize1; ----
872 ConstantSDNode *CN, *CN1; ----
873 ----
874 // See if Op's first operand matches (and $src1 , mask0). ----
875 if (And0.getOpcode() != ISD::AND) 0
876 return SDValue(); 0
877 ----
878 if (!(CN = dyn_cast(And0.getOperand(1))) || 0
879 !isShiftedMask_64(~CN->getSExtValue(), SMPos0, SMSize0)) 0
880 return SDValue(); 0
881 ----
882 // See if Op's second operand matches (and (shl $src, pos), mask1). ----
883 if (And1.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && 0
884 And1.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) { 0
885 ----
886 if (!(CN = dyn_cast(And1.getOperand(1))) || 0
887 !isShiftedMask_64(CN->getZExtValue(), SMPos1, SMSize1)) 0
888 return SDValue(); 0
889 ----
890 // The shift masks must have the same position and size. ----
891 if (SMPos0 != SMPos1 || SMSize0 != SMSize1) 0
892 return SDValue(); 0
893 ----
894 SDValue Shl = And1.getOperand(0); 0
895 ----
896 if (!(CN = dyn_cast(Shl.getOperand(1)))) 0
897 return SDValue(); 0
898 ----
899 unsigned Shamt = CN->getZExtValue(); 0
900 ----
901 // Return if the shift amount and the first bit position of mask are not the ----
902 // same. ----
903 EVT ValTy = N->getValueType(0); 0
904 if ((Shamt != SMPos0) || (SMPos0 + SMSize0 > ValTy.getSizeInBits())) 0
905 return SDValue(); 0
906 ----
907 SDLoc DL(N); 0
908 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ins, DL, ValTy, Shl.getOperand(0), 0
909 DAG.getConstant(SMPos0, DL, MVT::i32), 0
910 DAG.getConstant(SMSize0, DL, MVT::i32), 0
911 And0.getOperand(0)); 0
912 } else { 0
913 // Pattern match DINS. ----
914 // $dst = or (and $src, mask0), mask1 ----
915 // where mask0 = ((1 << SMSize0) -1) << SMPos0 ----
916 // => dins $dst, $src, pos, size ----
917 if (~CN->getSExtValue() == ((((int64_t)1 << SMSize0) - 1) << SMPos0) && 0
918 ((SMSize0 + SMPos0 <= 64 && Subtarget.hasMips64r2()) || 0
919 (SMSize0 + SMPos0 <= 32))) { 0
920 // Check if AND instruction has constant as argument ----
921 bool isConstCase = And1.getOpcode() != ISD::AND; 0
922 if (And1.getOpcode() == ISD::AND) { 0
923 if (!(CN1 = dyn_cast(And1->getOperand(1)))) 0
924 return SDValue(); 0
925 } else { ----
926 if (!(CN1 = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(1)))) 0
927 return SDValue(); 0
928 } ----
929 // Don't generate INS if constant OR operand doesn't fit into bits ----
930 // cleared by constant AND operand. ----
931 if (CN->getSExtValue() & CN1->getSExtValue()) 0
932 return SDValue(); 0
933 ----
934 SDLoc DL(N); 0
935 EVT ValTy = N->getOperand(0)->getValueType(0); 0
936 SDValue Const1; 0
937 SDValue SrlX; 0
938 if (!isConstCase) { 0
939 Const1 = DAG.getConstant(SMPos0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
940 SrlX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, And1->getValueType(0), And1, Const1); 0
941 } ----
942 return DAG.getNode( 0
943 MipsISD::Ins, DL, N->getValueType(0), ----
944 isConstCase ----
945 ? DAG.getConstant(CN1->getSExtValue() >> SMPos0, DL, ValTy) 0
946 : SrlX, ----
947 DAG.getConstant(SMPos0, DL, MVT::i32), 0
948 DAG.getConstant(ValTy.getSizeInBits() / 8 < 8 ? SMSize0 & 31 0
949 : SMSize0, ----
950 DL, MVT::i32), ----
951 And0->getOperand(0)); 0
952 ----
953 } 0
954 return SDValue(); 0
955 } ----
956 } ----
957 ----
958 static SDValue performMADD_MSUBCombine(SDNode *ROOTNode, SelectionDAG &CurDAG, 0
959 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
960 // ROOTNode must have a multiplication as an operand for the match to be ----
961 // successful. ----
962 if (ROOTNode->getOperand(0).getOpcode() != ISD::MUL && 0
963 ROOTNode->getOperand(1).getOpcode() != ISD::MUL) 0
964 return SDValue(); 0
965 ----
966 // In the case where we have a multiplication as the left operand of ----
967 // of a subtraction, we can't combine into a MipsISD::MSub node as the ----
968 // the instruction definition of msub(u) places the multiplication on ----
969 // on the right. ----
970 if (ROOTNode->getOpcode() == ISD::SUB && 0
971 ROOTNode->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::MUL) 0
972 return SDValue(); 0
973 ----
974 // We don't handle vector types here. ----
975 if (ROOTNode->getValueType(0).isVector()) 0
976 return SDValue(); 0
977 ----
978 // For MIPS64, madd / msub instructions are inefficent to use with 64 bit ----
979 // arithmetic. E.g. ----
980 // (add (mul a b) c) => ----
981 // let res = (madd (mthi (drotr c 32))x(mtlo c) a b) in ----
982 // MIPS64: (or (dsll (mfhi res) 32) (dsrl (dsll (mflo res) 32) 32) ----
983 // or ----
984 // MIPS64R2: (dins (mflo res) (mfhi res) 32 32) ----
985 // ----
986 // The overhead of setting up the Hi/Lo registers and reassembling the ----
987 // result makes this a dubious optimzation for MIPS64. The core of the ----
988 // problem is that Hi/Lo contain the upper and lower 32 bits of the ----
989 // operand and result. ----
990 // ----
991 // It requires a chain of 4 add/mul for MIPS64R2 to get better code ----
992 // density than doing it naively, 5 for MIPS64. Additionally, using ----
993 // madd/msub on MIPS64 requires the operands actually be 32 bit sign ----
994 // extended operands, not true 64 bit values. ----
995 // ----
996 // FIXME: For the moment, disable this completely for MIPS64. ----
997 if (Subtarget.hasMips64()) 0
998 return SDValue(); 0
999 ----
1000 SDValue Mult = ROOTNode->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::MUL 0
1001 ? ROOTNode->getOperand(0) 0
1002 : ROOTNode->getOperand(1); 0
1003 ----
1004 SDValue AddOperand = ROOTNode->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::MUL 0
1005 ? ROOTNode->getOperand(1) 0
1006 : ROOTNode->getOperand(0); 0
1007 ----
1008 // Transform this to a MADD only if the user of this node is the add. ----
1009 // If there are other users of the mul, this function returns here. ----
1010 if (!Mult.hasOneUse()) 0
1011 return SDValue(); 0
1012 ----
1013 // maddu and madd are unusual instructions in that on MIPS64 bits 63..31 ----
1014 // must be in canonical form, i.e. sign extended. For MIPS32, the operands ----
1015 // of the multiply must have 32 or more sign bits, otherwise we cannot ----
1016 // perform this optimization. We have to check this here as we're performing ----
1017 // this optimization pre-legalization. ----
1018 SDValue MultLHS = Mult->getOperand(0); 0
1019 SDValue MultRHS = Mult->getOperand(1); 0
1020 ----
1021 bool IsSigned = MultLHS->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND && 0
1022 MultRHS->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND; 0
1023 bool IsUnsigned = MultLHS->getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND && 0
1024 MultRHS->getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND; 0
1025 ----
1026 if (!IsSigned && !IsUnsigned) 0
1027 return SDValue(); 0
1028 ----
1029 // Initialize accumulator. ----
1030 SDLoc DL(ROOTNode); 0
1031 SDValue BottomHalf, TopHalf; 0
1032 std::tie(BottomHalf, TopHalf) = 0
1033 CurDAG.SplitScalar(AddOperand, DL, MVT::i32, MVT::i32); 0
1034 SDValue ACCIn = ----
1035 CurDAG.getNode(MipsISD::MTLOHI, DL, MVT::Untyped, BottomHalf, TopHalf); 0
1036 ----
1037 // Create MipsMAdd(u) / MipsMSub(u) node. ----
1038 bool IsAdd = ROOTNode->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD; 0
1039 unsigned Opcode = IsAdd ? (IsUnsigned ? MipsISD::MAddu : MipsISD::MAdd) 0
1040 : (IsUnsigned ? MipsISD::MSubu : MipsISD::MSub); ----
1041 SDValue MAddOps[3] = { ----
1042 CurDAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Mult->getOperand(0)), 0
1043 CurDAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32, Mult->getOperand(1)), ACCIn}; 0
1044 EVT VTs[2] = {MVT::i32, MVT::i32}; 0
1045 SDValue MAdd = CurDAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, VTs, MAddOps); 0
1046 ----
1047 SDValue ResLo = CurDAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFLO, DL, MVT::i32, MAdd); 0
1048 SDValue ResHi = CurDAG.getNode(MipsISD::MFHI, DL, MVT::i32, MAdd); 0
1049 SDValue Combined = ----
1050 CurDAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, MVT::i64, ResLo, ResHi); 0
1051 return Combined; 0
1052 } 0
1053 ----
1054 static SDValue performSUBCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
1055 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
1056 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
1057 // (sub v0 (mul v1, v2)) => (msub v1, v2, v0) ----
1058 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps()) { 0
1059 if (Subtarget.hasMips32() && !Subtarget.hasMips32r6() && 0
1060 !Subtarget.inMips16Mode() && N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64) 0
1061 return performMADD_MSUBCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget); 0
1062 ----
1063 return SDValue(); 0
1064 } ----
1065 ----
1066 return SDValue(); 0
1067 } ----
1068 ----
1069 static SDValue performADDCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
1070 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
1071 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
1072 // (add v0 (mul v1, v2)) => (madd v1, v2, v0) ----
1073 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps()) { 0
1074 if (Subtarget.hasMips32() && !Subtarget.hasMips32r6() && 0
1075 !Subtarget.inMips16Mode() && N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64) 0
1076 return performMADD_MSUBCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget); 0
1077 ----
1078 return SDValue(); 0
1079 } ----
1080 ----
1081 // (add v0, (add v1, abs_lo(tjt))) => (add (add v0, v1), abs_lo(tjt)) ----
1082 SDValue Add = N->getOperand(1); 0
1083 ----
1084 if (Add.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD) 0
1085 return SDValue(); 0
1086 ----
1087 SDValue Lo = Add.getOperand(1); 0
1088 ----
1089 if ((Lo.getOpcode() != MipsISD::Lo) || 0
1090 (Lo.getOperand(0).getOpcode() != ISD::TargetJumpTable)) 0
1091 return SDValue(); 0
1092 ----
1093 EVT ValTy = N->getValueType(0); 0
1094 SDLoc DL(N); 0
1095 ----
1096 SDValue Add1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, ValTy, N->getOperand(0), 0
1097 Add.getOperand(0)); 0
1098 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, ValTy, Add1, Lo); 0
1099 } 0

1101 static SDValue performSHLCombine(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
1102 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI, ----
1103 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
1104 // Pattern match CINS. ----
1105 // $dst = shl (and $src , imm), pos ----
1106 // => cins $dst, $src, pos, size ----
1107 ----
1108 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps() || !Subtarget.hasCnMips()) 0
1109 return SDValue(); 0
1110 ----
1111 SDValue FirstOperand = N->getOperand(0); 0
1112 unsigned FirstOperandOpc = FirstOperand.getOpcode(); 0
1113 SDValue SecondOperand = N->getOperand(1); 0
1114 EVT ValTy = N->getValueType(0); 0
1115 SDLoc DL(N); 0
1116 ----
1117 uint64_t Pos = 0; 0
1118 unsigned SMPos, SMSize; ----
1119 ConstantSDNode *CN; ----
1120 SDValue NewOperand; 0
1121 ----
1122 // The second operand of the shift must be an immediate. ----
1123 if (!(CN = dyn_cast(SecondOperand))) 0
1124 return SDValue(); 0
1125 ----
1126 Pos = CN->getZExtValue(); 0
1127 ----
1128 if (Pos >= ValTy.getSizeInBits()) 0
1129 return SDValue(); 0
1130 ----
1131 if (FirstOperandOpc != ISD::AND) 0
1132 return SDValue(); 0
1133 ----
1134 // AND's second operand must be a shifted mask. ----
1135 if (!(CN = dyn_cast(FirstOperand.getOperand(1))) || 0
1136 !isShiftedMask_64(CN->getZExtValue(), SMPos, SMSize)) 0
1137 return SDValue(); 0
1138 ----
1139 // Return if the shifted mask does not start at bit 0 or the sum of its size ----
1140 // and Pos exceeds the word's size. ----
1141 if (SMPos != 0 || SMSize > 32 || Pos + SMSize > ValTy.getSizeInBits()) 0
1142 return SDValue(); 0
1143 ----
1144 NewOperand = FirstOperand.getOperand(0); 0
1145 // SMSize is 'location' (position) in this case, not size. ----
1146 SMSize--; 0
1147 ----
1148 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::CIns, DL, ValTy, NewOperand, 0
1149 DAG.getConstant(Pos, DL, MVT::i32), 0
1150 DAG.getConstant(SMSize, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1151 } 0

1192 // We can use ANDI+SLTIU as a bit test. Y contains the bit position. ----
1193 // For MIPSR2 or later, we may be able to use the `ext` instruction or its' ----

1201 bool MipsTargetLowering::shouldFoldConstantShiftPairToMask( 0
1202 const SDNode *N, CombineLevel Level) const { ----
1203 assert(((N->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && 0
1204 N->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) || ----
1205 (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRL && ----
1206 N->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SHL)) && ----
1207 "Expected shift-shift mask"); ----
1208 ----
1209 if (N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector()) 0
1210 return false; 0
1211 return true; 0

1262 { ----

1267 ----
1268 static MachineBasicBlock *insertDivByZeroTrap(MachineInstr &MI, 0
1269 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ----
1270 const TargetInstrInfo &TII, ----
1271 bool Is64Bit, bool IsMicroMips) { ----
1272 if (NoZeroDivCheck) 0
1273 return &MBB; 0
1274 ----
1275 // Insert instruction "teq $divisor_reg, $zero, 7". ----
1276 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I(MI); 0
1277 MachineInstrBuilder MIB; 0
1278 MachineOperand &Divisor = MI.getOperand(2); 0
1279 MIB = BuildMI(MBB, std::next(I), MI.getDebugLoc(), 0
1280 TII.get(IsMicroMips ? Mips::TEQ_MM : Mips::TEQ)) ----
1281 .addReg(Divisor.getReg(), getKillRegState(Divisor.isKill())) 0
1282 .addReg(Mips::ZERO) 0
1283 .addImm(7); 0
1284 ----
1285 // Use the 32-bit sub-register if this is a 64-bit division. ----
1286 if (Is64Bit) 0
1287 MIB->getOperand(0).setSubReg(Mips::sub_32); 0
1288 ----
1289 // Clear Divisor's kill flag. ----
1290 Divisor.setIsKill(false); 0
1291 ----
1292 // We would normally delete the original instruction here but in this case ----
1293 // we only needed to inject an additional instruction rather than replace it. ----
1294 ----
1295 return &MBB; 0
1296 } ----

1469 // This function also handles Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I32 (when BinOpcode == 0), and ----
1470 // Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I32 (when Nand == true) ----
1471 MachineBasicBlock * ----
1472 MipsTargetLowering::emitAtomicBinary(MachineInstr &MI, 0
1473 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
1474 ----
1475 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent(); 0
1476 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
1477 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
1478 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1479 ----
1480 unsigned AtomicOp; ----
1481 bool NeedsAdditionalReg = false; 0
1482 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
1483 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I32: 0
1484 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I32_POSTRA; 0
1485 break; 0
1486 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I32: 0
1487 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I32_POSTRA; 0
1488 break; 0
1489 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I32: 0
1490 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I32_POSTRA; 0
1491 break; 0
1492 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I32: 0
1493 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I32_POSTRA; 0
1494 break; 0
1495 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I32: 0
1496 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I32_POSTRA; 0
1497 break; 0
1498 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I32: 0
1499 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I32_POSTRA; 0
1500 break; 0
1501 case Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I32: 0
1502 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I32_POSTRA; 0
1503 break; 0
1504 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I64: 0
1505 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I64_POSTRA; 0
1506 break; 0
1507 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I64: 0
1508 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I64_POSTRA; 0
1509 break; 0
1510 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I64: 0
1511 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I64_POSTRA; 0
1512 break; 0
1513 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I64: 0
1514 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I64_POSTRA; 0
1515 break; 0
1516 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I64: 0
1517 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I64_POSTRA; 0
1518 break; 0
1519 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I64: 0
1520 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I64_POSTRA; 0
1521 break; 0
1522 case Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I64: 0
1523 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I64_POSTRA; 0
1524 break; 0
1525 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN_I32: 0
1526 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN_I32_POSTRA; 0
1527 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1528 break; 0
1529 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX_I32: 0
1530 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX_I32_POSTRA; 0
1531 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1532 break; 0
1533 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN_I32: 0
1534 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN_I32_POSTRA; 0
1535 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1536 break; 0
1537 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX_I32: 0
1538 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX_I32_POSTRA; 0
1539 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1540 break; 0
1541 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN_I64: 0
1542 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN_I64_POSTRA; 0
1543 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1544 break; 0
1545 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX_I64: 0
1546 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX_I64_POSTRA; 0
1547 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1548 break; 0
1549 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN_I64: 0
1550 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN_I64_POSTRA; 0
1551 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1552 break; 0
1553 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX_I64: 0
1554 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX_I64_POSTRA; 0
1555 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1556 break; 0
1557 default: 0
1558 llvm_unreachable("Unknown pseudo atomic for replacement!"); 0
1559 } ----
1560 ----
1561 Register OldVal = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1562 Register Ptr = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1563 Register Incr = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1564 Register Scratch = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RegInfo.getRegClass(OldVal)); 0
1565 ----
1566 MachineBasicBlock::iterator II(MI); 0
1567 ----
1568 // The scratch registers here with the EarlyClobber | Define | Implicit ----
1569 // flags is used to persuade the register allocator and the machine ----
1570 // verifier to accept the usage of this register. This has to be a real ----
1571 // register which has an UNDEF value but is dead after the instruction which ----
1572 // is unique among the registers chosen for the instruction. ----
1573 ----
1574 // The EarlyClobber flag has the semantic properties that the operand it is ----
1575 // attached to is clobbered before the rest of the inputs are read. Hence it ----
1576 // must be unique among the operands to the instruction. ----
1577 // The Define flag is needed to coerce the machine verifier that an Undef ----
1578 // value isn't a problem. ----
1579 // The Dead flag is needed as the value in scratch isn't used by any other ----
1580 // instruction. Kill isn't used as Dead is more precise. ----
1581 // The implicit flag is here due to the interaction between the other flags ----
1582 // and the machine verifier. ----
1583 ----
1584 // For correctness purpose, a new pseudo is introduced here. We need this ----
1585 // new pseudo, so that FastRegisterAllocator does not see an ll/sc sequence ----
1586 // that is spread over >1 basic blocks. A register allocator which ----
1587 // introduces (or any codegen infact) a store, can violate the expectations ----
1588 // of the hardware. ----
1589 // ----
1590 // An atomic read-modify-write sequence starts with a linked load ----
1591 // instruction and ends with a store conditional instruction. The atomic ----
1592 // read-modify-write sequence fails if any of the following conditions ----
1593 // occur between the execution of ll and sc: ----
1594 // * A coherent store is completed by another process or coherent I/O ----
1595 // module into the block of synchronizable physical memory containing ----
1596 // the word. The size and alignment of the block is ----
1597 // implementation-dependent. ----
1598 // * A coherent store is executed between an LL and SC sequence on the ----
1599 // same processor to the block of synchornizable physical memory ----
1600 // containing the word. ----
1601 // ----
1602 ----
1603 Register PtrCopy = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RegInfo.getRegClass(Ptr)); 0
1604 Register IncrCopy = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RegInfo.getRegClass(Incr)); 0
1605 ----
1606 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), IncrCopy).addReg(Incr); 0
1607 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), PtrCopy).addReg(Ptr); 0
1608 ----
1609 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
1610 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(AtomicOp)) 0
1611 .addReg(OldVal, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber) 0
1612 .addReg(PtrCopy) 0
1613 .addReg(IncrCopy) 0
1614 .addReg(Scratch, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber | 0
1615 RegState::Implicit | RegState::Dead); 0
1616 if (NeedsAdditionalReg) { 0
1617 Register Scratch2 = ----
1618 RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RegInfo.getRegClass(OldVal)); 0
1619 MIB.addReg(Scratch2, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber | 0
1620 RegState::Implicit | RegState::Dead); ----
1621 } ----
1622 ----
1623 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
1624 ----
1625 return BB; 0
1626 } 0
1627 ----
1628 MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitSignExtendToI32InReg( 0
1629 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned Size, unsigned DstReg, ----
1630 unsigned SrcReg) const { ----
1631 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
1632 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1633 ----
1634 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r2() && Size == 1) { 0
1635 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SEB), DstReg).addReg(SrcReg); 0
1636 return BB; 0
1637 } ----
1638 ----
1639 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r2() && Size == 2) { 0
1640 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SEH), DstReg).addReg(SrcReg); 0
1641 return BB; 0
1642 } ----
1643 ----
1644 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent(); 0
1645 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
1646 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(MVT::i32); 0
1647 Register ScrReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1648 ----
1649 assert(Size < 32); 0
1650 int64_t ShiftImm = 32 - (Size * 8); 0
1651 ----
1652 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLL), ScrReg).addReg(SrcReg).addImm(ShiftImm); 0
1653 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SRA), DstReg).addReg(ScrReg).addImm(ShiftImm); 0
1654 ----
1655 return BB; 0
1656 } ----
1657 ----
1658 MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitAtomicBinaryPartword( 0
1659 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned Size) const { ----
1660 assert((Size == 1 || Size == 2) && 0
1661 "Unsupported size for EmitAtomicBinaryPartial."); ----
1662 ----
1663 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent(); 0
1664 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
1665 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(MVT::i32); 0
1666 const bool ArePtrs64bit = ABI.ArePtrs64bit(); 0
1667 const TargetRegisterClass *RCp = ----
1668 getRegClassFor(ArePtrs64bit ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32); 0
1669 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
1670 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1671 ----
1672 Register Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1673 Register Ptr = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1674 Register Incr = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1675 ----
1676 Register AlignedAddr = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RCp); 0
1677 Register ShiftAmt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1678 Register Mask = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1679 Register Mask2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1680 Register Incr2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1681 Register MaskLSB2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RCp); 0
1682 Register PtrLSB2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1683 Register MaskUpper = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1684 Register Scratch = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1685 Register Scratch2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1686 Register Scratch3 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1687 ----
1688 unsigned AtomicOp = 0; 0
1689 bool NeedsAdditionalReg = false; 0
1690 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
1691 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I8: 0
1692 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I8_POSTRA; 0
1693 break; 0
1694 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I16: 0
1695 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND_I16_POSTRA; 0
1696 break; 0
1697 case Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I8: 0
1698 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I8_POSTRA; 0
1699 break; 0
1700 case Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I16: 0
1701 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_SWAP_I16_POSTRA; 0
1702 break; 0
1703 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I8: 0
1704 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I8_POSTRA; 0
1705 break; 0
1706 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I16: 0
1707 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD_I16_POSTRA; 0
1708 break; 0
1709 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I8: 0
1710 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I8_POSTRA; 0
1711 break; 0
1712 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I16: 0
1713 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB_I16_POSTRA; 0
1714 break; 0
1715 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I8: 0
1716 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I8_POSTRA; 0
1717 break; 0
1718 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I16: 0
1719 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND_I16_POSTRA; 0
1720 break; 0
1721 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I8: 0
1722 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I8_POSTRA; 0
1723 break; 0
1724 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I16: 0
1725 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR_I16_POSTRA; 0
1726 break; 0
1727 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I8: 0
1728 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I8_POSTRA; 0
1729 break; 0
1730 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I16: 0
1731 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR_I16_POSTRA; 0
1732 break; 0
1733 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN_I8: 0
1734 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN_I8_POSTRA; 0
1735 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1736 break; 0
1737 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN_I16: 0
1738 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN_I16_POSTRA; 0
1739 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1740 break; 0
1741 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX_I8: 0
1742 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX_I8_POSTRA; 0
1743 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1744 break; 0
1745 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX_I16: 0
1746 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX_I16_POSTRA; 0
1747 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1748 break; 0
1749 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN_I8: 0
1750 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN_I8_POSTRA; 0
1751 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1752 break; 0
1753 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN_I16: 0
1754 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN_I16_POSTRA; 0
1755 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1756 break; 0
1757 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX_I8: 0
1758 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX_I8_POSTRA; 0
1759 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1760 break; 0
1761 case Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX_I16: 0
1762 AtomicOp = Mips::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX_I16_POSTRA; 0
1763 NeedsAdditionalReg = true; 0
1764 break; 0
1765 default: 0
1766 llvm_unreachable("Unknown subword atomic pseudo for expansion!"); 0
1767 } ----
1768 ----
1769 // insert new blocks after the current block ----
1770 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock(); 0
1771 MachineBasicBlock *exitMBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
1772 MachineFunction::iterator It = ++BB->getIterator(); 0
1773 MF->insert(It, exitMBB); 0
1774 ----
1775 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to exitMBB. ----
1776 exitMBB->splice(exitMBB->begin(), BB, 0
1777 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), BB->end()); ----
1778 exitMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB); 0
1779 ----
1780 BB->addSuccessor(exitMBB, BranchProbability::getOne()); 0
1781 ----
1782 // thisMBB: ----
1783 // addiu masklsb2,$0,-4 # 0xfffffffc ----
1784 // and alignedaddr,ptr,masklsb2 ----
1785 // andi ptrlsb2,ptr,3 ----
1786 // sll shiftamt,ptrlsb2,3 ----
1787 // ori maskupper,$0,255 # 0xff ----
1788 // sll mask,maskupper,shiftamt ----
1789 // nor mask2,$0,mask ----
1790 // sll incr2,incr,shiftamt ----
1791 ----
1792 int64_t MaskImm = (Size == 1) ? 255 : 65535; 0
1793 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(ABI.GetPtrAddiuOp()), MaskLSB2) 0
1794 .addReg(ABI.GetNullPtr()).addImm(-4); 0
1795 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(ABI.GetPtrAndOp()), AlignedAddr) 0
1796 .addReg(Ptr).addReg(MaskLSB2); 0
1797 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ANDi), PtrLSB2) 0
1798 .addReg(Ptr, 0, ArePtrs64bit ? Mips::sub_32 : 0).addImm(3); 0
1799 if (Subtarget.isLittle()) { 0
1800 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLL), ShiftAmt).addReg(PtrLSB2).addImm(3); 0
1801 } else { ----
1802 Register Off = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1803 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::XORi), Off) 0
1804 .addReg(PtrLSB2).addImm((Size == 1) ? 3 : 2); 0
1805 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLL), ShiftAmt).addReg(Off).addImm(3); 0
1806 } ----
1807 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ORi), MaskUpper) 0
1808 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(MaskImm); 0
1809 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLLV), Mask) 0
1810 .addReg(MaskUpper).addReg(ShiftAmt); 0
1811 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::NOR), Mask2).addReg(Mips::ZERO).addReg(Mask); 0
1812 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLLV), Incr2).addReg(Incr).addReg(ShiftAmt); 0
1813 ----
1814 ----
1815 // The purposes of the flags on the scratch registers is explained in ----
1816 // emitAtomicBinary. In summary, we need a scratch register which is going to ----
1817 // be undef, that is unique among registers chosen for the instruction. ----
1818 ----
1819 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
1820 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(AtomicOp)) 0
1821 .addReg(Dest, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber) 0
1822 .addReg(AlignedAddr) 0
1823 .addReg(Incr2) 0
1824 .addReg(Mask) 0
1825 .addReg(Mask2) 0
1826 .addReg(ShiftAmt) 0
1827 .addReg(Scratch, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define | 0
1828 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit) ----
1829 .addReg(Scratch2, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define | 0
1830 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit) ----
1831 .addReg(Scratch3, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define | 0
1832 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit); 0
1833 if (NeedsAdditionalReg) { 0
1834 Register Scratch4 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1835 MIB.addReg(Scratch4, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define | 0
1836 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit); ----
1837 } ----
1838 ----
1839 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The instruction is gone now. 0
1840 ----
1841 return exitMBB; 0
1842 } 0
1843 ----
1844 // Lower atomic compare and swap to a pseudo instruction, taking care to ----
1845 // define a scratch register for the pseudo instruction's expansion. The ----
1846 // instruction is expanded after the register allocator as to prevent ----
1847 // the insertion of stores between the linked load and the store conditional. ----
1848 ----
1849 MachineBasicBlock * ----
1850 MipsTargetLowering::emitAtomicCmpSwap(MachineInstr &MI, 0
1851 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
1852 ----
1853 assert((MI.getOpcode() == Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I32 || 0
1854 MI.getOpcode() == Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I64) && ----
1855 "Unsupported atomic pseudo for EmitAtomicCmpSwap."); ----
1856 ----
1857 const unsigned Size = MI.getOpcode() == Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I32 ? 4 : 8; 0
1858 ----
1859 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent(); 0
1860 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
1861 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(MVT::getIntegerVT(Size * 8)); 0
1862 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
1863 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1864 ----
1865 unsigned AtomicOp = MI.getOpcode() == Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I32 0
1866 ? Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I32_POSTRA 0
1867 : Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I64_POSTRA; 0
1868 Register Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1869 Register Ptr = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1870 Register OldVal = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1871 Register NewVal = MI.getOperand(3).getReg(); 0
1872 ----
1873 Register Scratch = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1874 MachineBasicBlock::iterator II(MI); 0
1875 ----
1876 // We need to create copies of the various registers and kill them at the ----
1877 // atomic pseudo. If the copies are not made, when the atomic is expanded ----
1878 // after fast register allocation, the spills will end up outside of the ----
1879 // blocks that their values are defined in, causing livein errors. ----
1880 ----
1881 Register PtrCopy = MRI.createVirtualRegister(MRI.getRegClass(Ptr)); 0
1882 Register OldValCopy = MRI.createVirtualRegister(MRI.getRegClass(OldVal)); 0
1883 Register NewValCopy = MRI.createVirtualRegister(MRI.getRegClass(NewVal)); 0
1884 ----
1885 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), PtrCopy).addReg(Ptr); 0
1886 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), OldValCopy).addReg(OldVal); 0
1887 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY), NewValCopy).addReg(NewVal); 0
1888 ----
1889 // The purposes of the flags on the scratch registers is explained in ----
1890 // emitAtomicBinary. In summary, we need a scratch register which is going to ----
1891 // be undef, that is unique among registers chosen for the instruction. ----
1892 ----
1893 BuildMI(*BB, II, DL, TII->get(AtomicOp)) 0
1894 .addReg(Dest, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber) 0
1895 .addReg(PtrCopy, RegState::Kill) 0
1896 .addReg(OldValCopy, RegState::Kill) 0
1897 .addReg(NewValCopy, RegState::Kill) 0
1898 .addReg(Scratch, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define | 0
1899 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit); ----
1900 ----
1901 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The instruction is gone now. 0
1902 ----
1903 return BB; 0
1904 } 0
1905 ----
1906 MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitAtomicCmpSwapPartword( 0
1907 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, unsigned Size) const { ----
1908 assert((Size == 1 || Size == 2) && 0
1909 "Unsupported size for EmitAtomicCmpSwapPartial."); ----
1910 ----
1911 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent(); 0
1912 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
1913 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(MVT::i32); 0
1914 const bool ArePtrs64bit = ABI.ArePtrs64bit(); 0
1915 const TargetRegisterClass *RCp = ----
1916 getRegClassFor(ArePtrs64bit ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32); 0
1917 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
1918 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1919 ----
1920 Register Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1921 Register Ptr = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1922 Register CmpVal = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1923 Register NewVal = MI.getOperand(3).getReg(); 0
1924 ----
1925 Register AlignedAddr = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RCp); 0
1926 Register ShiftAmt = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1927 Register Mask = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1928 Register Mask2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1929 Register ShiftedCmpVal = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1930 Register ShiftedNewVal = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1931 Register MaskLSB2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RCp); 0
1932 Register PtrLSB2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1933 Register MaskUpper = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1934 Register MaskedCmpVal = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1935 Register MaskedNewVal = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1936 unsigned AtomicOp = MI.getOpcode() == Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I8 0
1937 ? Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I8_POSTRA 0
1938 : Mips::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_I16_POSTRA; 0
1939 ----
1940 // The scratch registers here with the EarlyClobber | Define | Dead | Implicit ----
1941 // flags are used to coerce the register allocator and the machine verifier to ----
1942 // accept the usage of these registers. ----
1943 // The EarlyClobber flag has the semantic properties that the operand it is ----
1944 // attached to is clobbered before the rest of the inputs are read. Hence it ----
1945 // must be unique among the operands to the instruction. ----
1946 // The Define flag is needed to coerce the machine verifier that an Undef ----
1947 // value isn't a problem. ----
1948 // The Dead flag is needed as the value in scratch isn't used by any other ----
1949 // instruction. Kill isn't used as Dead is more precise. ----
1950 Register Scratch = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1951 Register Scratch2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1952 ----
1953 // insert new blocks after the current block ----
1954 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock(); 0
1955 MachineBasicBlock *exitMBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
1956 MachineFunction::iterator It = ++BB->getIterator(); 0
1957 MF->insert(It, exitMBB); 0
1958 ----
1959 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to exitMBB. ----
1960 exitMBB->splice(exitMBB->begin(), BB, 0
1961 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), BB->end()); ----
1962 exitMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB); 0
1963 ----
1964 BB->addSuccessor(exitMBB, BranchProbability::getOne()); 0
1965 ----
1966 // thisMBB: ----
1967 // addiu masklsb2,$0,-4 # 0xfffffffc ----
1968 // and alignedaddr,ptr,masklsb2 ----
1969 // andi ptrlsb2,ptr,3 ----
1970 // xori ptrlsb2,ptrlsb2,3 # Only for BE ----
1971 // sll shiftamt,ptrlsb2,3 ----
1972 // ori maskupper,$0,255 # 0xff ----
1973 // sll mask,maskupper,shiftamt ----
1974 // nor mask2,$0,mask ----
1975 // andi maskedcmpval,cmpval,255 ----
1976 // sll shiftedcmpval,maskedcmpval,shiftamt ----
1977 // andi maskednewval,newval,255 ----
1978 // sll shiftednewval,maskednewval,shiftamt ----
1979 int64_t MaskImm = (Size == 1) ? 255 : 65535; 0
1980 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(ArePtrs64bit ? Mips::DADDiu : Mips::ADDiu), MaskLSB2) 0
1981 .addReg(ABI.GetNullPtr()).addImm(-4); 0
1982 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(ArePtrs64bit ? Mips::AND64 : Mips::AND), AlignedAddr) 0
1983 .addReg(Ptr).addReg(MaskLSB2); 0
1984 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ANDi), PtrLSB2) 0
1985 .addReg(Ptr, 0, ArePtrs64bit ? Mips::sub_32 : 0).addImm(3); 0
1986 if (Subtarget.isLittle()) { 0
1987 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLL), ShiftAmt).addReg(PtrLSB2).addImm(3); 0
1988 } else { ----
1989 Register Off = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1990 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::XORi), Off) 0
1991 .addReg(PtrLSB2).addImm((Size == 1) ? 3 : 2); 0
1992 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLL), ShiftAmt).addReg(Off).addImm(3); 0
1993 } ----
1994 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ORi), MaskUpper) 0
1995 .addReg(Mips::ZERO).addImm(MaskImm); 0
1996 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLLV), Mask) 0
1997 .addReg(MaskUpper).addReg(ShiftAmt); 0
1998 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::NOR), Mask2).addReg(Mips::ZERO).addReg(Mask); 0
1999 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ANDi), MaskedCmpVal) 0
2000 .addReg(CmpVal).addImm(MaskImm); 0
2001 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLLV), ShiftedCmpVal) 0
2002 .addReg(MaskedCmpVal).addReg(ShiftAmt); 0
2003 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::ANDi), MaskedNewVal) 0
2004 .addReg(NewVal).addImm(MaskImm); 0
2005 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::SLLV), ShiftedNewVal) 0
2006 .addReg(MaskedNewVal).addReg(ShiftAmt); 0
2007 ----
2008 // The purposes of the flags on the scratch registers are explained in ----
2009 // emitAtomicBinary. In summary, we need a scratch register which is going to ----
2010 // be undef, that is unique among the register chosen for the instruction. ----
2011 ----
2012 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(AtomicOp)) 0
2013 .addReg(Dest, RegState::Define | RegState::EarlyClobber) 0
2014 .addReg(AlignedAddr) 0
2015 .addReg(Mask) 0
2016 .addReg(ShiftedCmpVal) 0
2017 .addReg(Mask2) 0
2018 .addReg(ShiftedNewVal) 0
2019 .addReg(ShiftAmt) 0
2020 .addReg(Scratch, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define | 0
2021 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit) ----
2022 .addReg(Scratch2, RegState::EarlyClobber | RegState::Define | 0
2023 RegState::Dead | RegState::Implicit); ----
2024 ----
2025 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The instruction is gone now. 0
2026 ----
2027 return exitMBB; 0
2028 } 0

2030 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerBRCOND(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2031 // The first operand is the chain, the second is the condition, the third is ----
2032 // the block to branch to if the condition is true. ----
2033 SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2034 SDValue Dest = Op.getOperand(2); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2035 SDLoc DL(Op); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2036 ----
2037 assert(!Subtarget.hasMips32r6() && !Subtarget.hasMips64r6()); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2038 SDValue CondRes = createFPCmp(DAG, Op.getOperand(1)); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2039 ----
2040 // Return if flag is not set by a floating point comparison. ----
2041 if (CondRes.getOpcode() != MipsISD::FPCmp) 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2042 return Op; 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2043 ----

2051 FCC0, Dest, CondRes); 0

2054 SDValue MipsTargetLowering:: 0
2055 lowerSELECT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const ----
2056 { ----
2057 assert(!Subtarget.hasMips32r6() && !Subtarget.hasMips64r6()); 0
2058 SDValue Cond = createFPCmp(DAG, Op.getOperand(0)); 0
2059 ----
2060 // Return if flag is not set by a floating point comparison. ----
2061 if (Cond.getOpcode() != MipsISD::FPCmp) 0
2062 return Op; 0
2063 ----
2064 return createCMovFP(DAG, Cond, Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2), 0
2065 SDLoc(Op)); 0

2068 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerSETCC(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const { 0
2069 assert(!Subtarget.hasMips32r6() && !Subtarget.hasMips64r6()); 0
2070 SDValue Cond = createFPCmp(DAG, Op); 0
2071 ----
2072 assert(Cond.getOpcode() == MipsISD::FPCmp && 0
2073 "Floating point operand expected."); ----
2074 ----
2075 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2076 SDValue True = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2077 SDValue False = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2078 ----
2079 return createCMovFP(DAG, Cond, True, False, DL); 0

2081 ----
2082 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerGlobalAddress(SDValue Op, 0
2083 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
2084 EVT Ty = Op.getValueType(); 0
2085 GlobalAddressSDNode *N = cast(Op); 0
2086 const GlobalValue *GV = N->getGlobal(); 0
2087 ----
2088 if (!isPositionIndependent()) { 0
2089 const MipsTargetObjectFile *TLOF = ----
2090 static_cast( ----
2091 getTargetMachine().getObjFileLowering()); 0
2092 const GlobalObject *GO = GV->getAliaseeObject(); 0
2093 if (GO && TLOF->IsGlobalInSmallSection(GO, getTargetMachine())) 0
2094 // %gp_rel relocation ----
2095 return getAddrGPRel(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN64()); 0
2096 ----
2097 // %hi/%lo relocation ----
2098 return Subtarget.hasSym32() ? getAddrNonPIC(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG) 0
2099 // %highest/%higher/%hi/%lo relocation ----
2100 : getAddrNonPICSym64(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG); 0
2101 } ----
2102 ----
2103 // Every other architecture would use shouldAssumeDSOLocal in here, but ----
2104 // mips is special. ----
2105 // * In PIC code mips requires got loads even for local statics! ----
2106 // * To save on got entries, for local statics the got entry contains the ----
2107 // page and an additional add instruction takes care of the low bits. ----
2108 // * It is legal to access a hidden symbol with a non hidden undefined, ----
2109 // so one cannot guarantee that all access to a hidden symbol will know ----
2110 // it is hidden. ----
2111 // * Mips linkers don't support creating a page and a full got entry for ----
2112 // the same symbol. ----
2113 // * Given all that, we have to use a full got entry for hidden symbols :-( ----
2114 if (GV->hasLocalLinkage()) 0
2115 return getAddrLocal(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64()); 0
2116 ----
2117 if (Subtarget.useXGOT()) 0
2118 return getAddrGlobalLargeGOT( 0
2119 N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_GOT_HI16, MipsII::MO_GOT_LO16, 0
2120 DAG.getEntryNode(), ----
2121 MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(DAG.getMachineFunction())); 0
2122 ----
2123 return getAddrGlobal( 0
2124 N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, 0
2125 (ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64()) ? MipsII::MO_GOT_DISP : MipsII::MO_GOT, 0
2126 DAG.getEntryNode(), MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(DAG.getMachineFunction())); 0
2127 } ----
2128 ----
2129 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerBlockAddress(SDValue Op, 0
2130 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
2131 BlockAddressSDNode *N = cast(Op); 0
2132 EVT Ty = Op.getValueType(); 0
2133 ----
2134 if (!isPositionIndependent()) 0
2135 return Subtarget.hasSym32() ? getAddrNonPIC(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG) 0
2136 : getAddrNonPICSym64(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG); 0
2137 ----
2138 return getAddrLocal(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64()); 0
2139 } ----
2140 ----
2141 SDValue MipsTargetLowering:: 0
2142 lowerGlobalTLSAddress(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const ----
2143 { ----
2144 // If the relocation model is PIC, use the General Dynamic TLS Model or ----
2145 // Local Dynamic TLS model, otherwise use the Initial Exec or ----
2146 // Local Exec TLS Model. ----
2147 ----
2148 GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = cast(Op); 0
2149 if (DAG.getTarget().useEmulatedTLS()) 0
2150 return LowerToTLSEmulatedModel(GA, DAG); 0
2151 ----
2152 SDLoc DL(GA); 0
2153 const GlobalValue *GV = GA->getGlobal(); 0
2154 EVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()); 0
2155 ----
2156 TLSModel::Model model = getTargetMachine().getTLSModel(GV); 0
2157 ----
2158 if (model == TLSModel::GeneralDynamic || model == TLSModel::LocalDynamic) { 0
2159 // General Dynamic and Local Dynamic TLS Model. ----
2160 unsigned Flag = (model == TLSModel::LocalDynamic) ? MipsII::MO_TLSLDM 0
2161 : MipsII::MO_TLSGD; ----
2162 ----
2163 SDValue TGA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0, Flag); 0
2164 SDValue Argument = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Wrapper, DL, PtrVT, 0
2165 getGlobalReg(DAG, PtrVT), TGA); ----
2166 unsigned PtrSize = PtrVT.getSizeInBits(); 0
2167 IntegerType *PtrTy = Type::getIntNTy(*DAG.getContext(), PtrSize); 0
2168 ----
2169 SDValue TlsGetAddr = DAG.getExternalSymbol("__tls_get_addr", PtrVT); 0
2170 ----
2171 ArgListTy Args; 0
2172 ArgListEntry Entry; 0
2173 Entry.Node = Argument; 0
2174 Entry.Ty = PtrTy; 0
2175 Args.push_back(Entry); 0
2176 ----
2177 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG); 0
2178 CLI.setDebugLoc(DL) 0
2179 .setChain(DAG.getEntryNode()) 0
2180 .setLibCallee(CallingConv::C, PtrTy, TlsGetAddr, std::move(Args)); 0
2181 std::pair CallResult = LowerCallTo(CLI); 0
2182 ----
2183 SDValue Ret = CallResult.first; 0
2184 ----
2185 if (model != TLSModel::LocalDynamic) 0
2186 return Ret; 0
2187 ----
2188 SDValue TGAHi = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0, 0
2189 MipsII::MO_DTPREL_HI); ----
2190 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::TlsHi, DL, PtrVT, TGAHi); 0
2191 SDValue TGALo = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0, 0
2192 MipsII::MO_DTPREL_LO); ----
2193 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Lo, DL, PtrVT, TGALo); 0
2194 SDValue Add = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, Hi, Ret); 0
2195 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, Add, Lo); 0
2196 } 0
2197 ----
2198 SDValue Offset; 0
2199 if (model == TLSModel::InitialExec) { 0
2200 // Initial Exec TLS Model ----
2201 SDValue TGA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0, 0
2202 MipsII::MO_GOTTPREL); ----
2203 TGA = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Wrapper, DL, PtrVT, getGlobalReg(DAG, PtrVT), 0
2204 TGA); ----
2205 Offset = 0
2206 DAG.getLoad(PtrVT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(), TGA, MachinePointerInfo()); 0
2207 } else { ----
2208 // Local Exec TLS Model ----
2209 assert(model == TLSModel::LocalExec); 0
2210 SDValue TGAHi = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0, 0
2211 MipsII::MO_TPREL_HI); ----
2212 SDValue TGALo = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0, 0
2213 MipsII::MO_TPREL_LO); ----
2214 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::TlsHi, DL, PtrVT, TGAHi); 0
2215 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Lo, DL, PtrVT, TGALo); 0
2216 Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, Hi, Lo); 0
2217 } ----
2218 ----
2219 SDValue ThreadPointer = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ThreadPointer, DL, PtrVT); 0
2220 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, ThreadPointer, Offset); 0
2221 } 0

2259 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerVASTART(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const { 0
2260 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction(); 0
2261 MipsFunctionInfo *FuncInfo = MF.getInfo(); 0
2262 ----
2263 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2264 SDValue FI = DAG.getFrameIndex(FuncInfo->getVarArgsFrameIndex(), 0
2265 getPointerTy(MF.getDataLayout())); 0
2266 ----
2267 // vastart just stores the address of the VarArgsFrameIndex slot into the ----
2268 // memory location argument. ----
2269 const Value *SV = cast(Op.getOperand(2))->getValue(); 0

2273 ----
2274 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerVAARG(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const { 0
2275 SDNode *Node = Op.getNode(); 0
2276 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2277 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0); 0
2278 SDValue VAListPtr = Node->getOperand(1); 0
2279 const Align Align = ----
2280 llvm::MaybeAlign(Node->getConstantOperandVal(3)).valueOrOne(); 0
2281 const Value *SV = cast(Node->getOperand(2))->getValue(); 0
2282 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
2283 unsigned ArgSlotSizeInBytes = (ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64()) ? 8 : 4; 0
2284 ----
2285 SDValue VAListLoad = DAG.getLoad(getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()), DL, Chain, 0
2286 VAListPtr, MachinePointerInfo(SV)); ----
2287 SDValue VAList = VAListLoad; 0
2288 ----
2289 // Re-align the pointer if necessary. ----
2290 // It should only ever be necessary for 64-bit types on O32 since the minimum ----
2291 // argument alignment is the same as the maximum type alignment for N32/N64. ----
2292 // ----
2293 // FIXME: We currently align too often. The code generator doesn't notice ----
2294 // when the pointer is still aligned from the last va_arg (or pair of ----
2295 // va_args for the i64 on O32 case). ----
2296 if (Align > getMinStackArgumentAlignment()) { 0
2297 VAList = DAG.getNode( 0
2298 ISD::ADD, DL, VAList.getValueType(), VAList, ----
2299 DAG.getConstant(Align.value() - 1, DL, VAList.getValueType())); 0
2300 ----
2301 VAList = DAG.getNode( 0
2302 ISD::AND, DL, VAList.getValueType(), VAList, ----
2303 DAG.getConstant(-(int64_t)Align.value(), DL, VAList.getValueType())); 0
2304 } ----
2305 ----
2306 // Increment the pointer, VAList, to the next vaarg. ----
2307 auto &TD = DAG.getDataLayout(); 0
2308 unsigned ArgSizeInBytes = ----
2309 TD.getTypeAllocSize(VT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext())); 0
2310 SDValue Tmp3 = ----
2311 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VAList.getValueType(), VAList, 0
2312 DAG.getConstant(alignTo(ArgSizeInBytes, ArgSlotSizeInBytes), ----
2313 DL, VAList.getValueType())); ----
2314 // Store the incremented VAList to the legalized pointer ----
2315 Chain = DAG.getStore(VAListLoad.getValue(1), DL, Tmp3, VAListPtr, 0
2316 MachinePointerInfo(SV)); ----
2317 ----
2318 // In big-endian mode we must adjust the pointer when the load size is smaller ----
2319 // than the argument slot size. We must also reduce the known alignment to ----
2320 // match. For example in the N64 ABI, we must add 4 bytes to the offset to get ----
2321 // the correct half of the slot, and reduce the alignment from 8 (slot ----
2322 // alignment) down to 4 (type alignment). ----
2323 if (!Subtarget.isLittle() && ArgSizeInBytes < ArgSlotSizeInBytes) { 0
2324 unsigned Adjustment = ArgSlotSizeInBytes - ArgSizeInBytes; 0
2325 VAList = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VAListPtr.getValueType(), VAList, 0
2326 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(Adjustment, DL)); ----
2327 } ----
2328 // Load the actual argument out of the pointer VAList ----
2329 return DAG.getLoad(VT, DL, Chain, VAList, MachinePointerInfo()); 0
2330 } 0
2331 ----
2332 static SDValue lowerFCOPYSIGN32(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
2333 bool HasExtractInsert) { ----
2334 EVT TyX = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType(); 0
2335 EVT TyY = Op.getOperand(1).getValueType(); 0
2336 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2337 SDValue Const1 = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2338 SDValue Const31 = DAG.getConstant(31, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2339 SDValue Res; 0
2340 ----
2341 // If operand is of type f64, extract the upper 32-bit. Otherwise, bitcast it ----
2342 // to i32. ----
2343 SDValue X = (TyX == MVT::f32) ? 0
2344 DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0)) : 0
2345 DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0), 0
2346 Const1); 0
2347 SDValue Y = (TyY == MVT::f32) ? 0
2348 DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(1)) : 0
2349 DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(1), 0
2350 Const1); 0
2351 ----
2352 if (HasExtractInsert) { 0
2353 // ext E, Y, 31, 1 ; extract bit31 of Y ----
2354 // ins X, E, 31, 1 ; insert extracted bit at bit31 of X ----
2355 SDValue E = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ext, DL, MVT::i32, Y, Const31, Const1); 0
2356 Res = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ins, DL, MVT::i32, E, Const31, Const1, X); 0
2357 } else { ----
2358 // sll SllX, X, 1 ----
2359 // srl SrlX, SllX, 1 ----
2360 // srl SrlY, Y, 31 ----
2361 // sll SllY, SrlX, 31 ----
2362 // or Or, SrlX, SllY ----
2363 SDValue SllX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i32, X, Const1); 0
2364 SDValue SrlX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i32, SllX, Const1); 0
2365 SDValue SrlY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i32, Y, Const31); 0
2366 SDValue SllY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i32, SrlY, Const31); 0
2367 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, MVT::i32, SrlX, SllY); 0
2368 } ----
2369 ----
2370 if (TyX == MVT::f32) 0
2371 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, Op.getOperand(0).getValueType(), Res); 0
2372 ----
2373 SDValue LowX = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, 0
2374 Op.getOperand(0), 0
2375 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2376 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, LowX, Res); 0
2377 } 0
2378 ----
2379 static SDValue lowerFCOPYSIGN64(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
2380 bool HasExtractInsert) { ----
2381 unsigned WidthX = Op.getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits(); 0
2382 unsigned WidthY = Op.getOperand(1).getValueSizeInBits(); 0
2383 EVT TyX = MVT::getIntegerVT(WidthX), TyY = MVT::getIntegerVT(WidthY); 0
2384 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2385 SDValue Const1 = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2386 ----
2387 // Bitcast to integer nodes. ----
2388 SDValue X = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, TyX, Op.getOperand(0)); 0
2389 SDValue Y = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, TyY, Op.getOperand(1)); 0
2390 ----
2391 if (HasExtractInsert) { 0
2392 // ext E, Y, width(Y) - 1, 1 ; extract bit width(Y)-1 of Y ----
2393 // ins X, E, width(X) - 1, 1 ; insert extracted bit at bit width(X)-1 of X ----
2394 SDValue E = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ext, DL, TyY, Y, 0
2395 DAG.getConstant(WidthY - 1, DL, MVT::i32), Const1); 0
2396 ----
2397 if (WidthX > WidthY) 0
2398 E = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, TyX, E); 0
2399 else if (WidthY > WidthX) 0
2400 E = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, TyX, E); 0
2401 ----
2402 SDValue I = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ins, DL, TyX, E, 0
2403 DAG.getConstant(WidthX - 1, DL, MVT::i32), Const1, 0
2404 X); ----
2405 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, Op.getOperand(0).getValueType(), I); 0
2406 } ----
2407 ----
2408 // (d)sll SllX, X, 1 ----
2409 // (d)srl SrlX, SllX, 1 ----
2410 // (d)srl SrlY, Y, width(Y)-1 ----
2411 // (d)sll SllY, SrlX, width(Y)-1 ----
2412 // or Or, SrlX, SllY ----
2413 SDValue SllX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, TyX, X, Const1); 0
2414 SDValue SrlX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, TyX, SllX, Const1); 0
2415 SDValue SrlY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, TyY, Y, 0
2416 DAG.getConstant(WidthY - 1, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2417 ----
2418 if (WidthX > WidthY) 0
2419 SrlY = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, TyX, SrlY); 0
2420 else if (WidthY > WidthX) 0
2421 SrlY = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, TyX, SrlY); 0
2422 ----
2423 SDValue SllY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, TyX, SrlY, 0
2424 DAG.getConstant(WidthX - 1, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2425 SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, TyX, SrlX, SllY); 0
2426 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, Op.getOperand(0).getValueType(), Or); 0
2427 } 0

2429 SDValue ----
2430 MipsTargetLowering::lowerFCOPYSIGN(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const { 0
2431 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit()) 0
2432 return lowerFCOPYSIGN64(Op, DAG, Subtarget.hasExtractInsert()); 0
2433 ----
2434 return lowerFCOPYSIGN32(Op, DAG, Subtarget.hasExtractInsert()); 0
2435 } ----

2437 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerFABS32(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
2438 bool HasExtractInsert) const { ----
2439 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2440 SDValue Res, Const1 = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2441 ----
2442 if (DAG.getTarget().Options.NoNaNsFPMath || Subtarget.inAbs2008Mode()) 0
2443 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::FAbs, DL, Op.getValueType(), Op.getOperand(0)); 0
2444 ----
2445 // If operand is of type f64, extract the upper 32-bit. Otherwise, bitcast it ----
2446 // to i32. ----
2447 SDValue X = (Op.getValueType() == MVT::f32) 0
2448 ? DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0)) 0
2449 : DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, 0
2450 Op.getOperand(0), Const1); 0
2451 ----
2452 // Clear MSB. ----
2453 if (HasExtractInsert) 0
2454 Res = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ins, DL, MVT::i32, 0
2455 DAG.getRegister(Mips::ZERO, MVT::i32), 0
2456 DAG.getConstant(31, DL, MVT::i32), Const1, X); 0
2457 else { ----
2458 // TODO: Provide DAG patterns which transform (and x, cst) ----
2459 // back to a (shl (srl x (clz cst)) (clz cst)) sequence. ----
2460 SDValue SllX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i32, X, Const1); 0
2461 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i32, SllX, Const1); 0
2462 } ----
2463 ----
2464 if (Op.getValueType() == MVT::f32) 0
2465 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::f32, Res); 0
2466 ----
2467 // FIXME: For mips32r2, the sequence of (BuildPairF64 (ins (ExtractElementF64 ----
2468 // Op 1), $zero, 31 1) (ExtractElementF64 Op 0)) and the Op has one use, we ----
2469 // should be able to drop the usage of mfc1/mtc1 and rewrite the register in ----
2470 // place. ----
2471 SDValue LowX = ----
2472 DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(0), 0
2473 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2474 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, LowX, Res); 0
2475 } 0
2476 ----
2477 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerFABS64(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
2478 bool HasExtractInsert) const { ----
2479 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2480 SDValue Res, Const1 = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2481 ----
2482 if (DAG.getTarget().Options.NoNaNsFPMath || Subtarget.inAbs2008Mode()) 0
2483 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::FAbs, DL, Op.getValueType(), Op.getOperand(0)); 0
2484 ----
2485 // Bitcast to integer node. ----
2486 SDValue X = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i64, Op.getOperand(0)); 0
2487 ----
2488 // Clear MSB. ----
2489 if (HasExtractInsert) 0
2490 Res = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Ins, DL, MVT::i64, 0

2492 DAG.getConstant(63, DL, MVT::i32), Const1, X); 0
2493 else { ----

2495 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i64, SllX, Const1); 0

2497 ----
2498 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::f64, Res); 0

2508 SDValue MipsTargetLowering:: 0
2509 lowerFRAMEADDR(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
2510 // check the depth ----
2511 if (cast(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue() != 0) { 0
2512 DAG.getContext()->emitError( 0
2513 "return address can be determined only for current frame"); ----
2514 return SDValue(); 0
2515 } ----
2516 ----
2517 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo(); 0
2518 MFI.setFrameAddressIsTaken(true); 0
2519 EVT VT = Op.getValueType(); 0
2520 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2521 SDValue FrameAddr = DAG.getCopyFromReg( 0
2522 DAG.getEntryNode(), DL, ABI.IsN64() ? Mips::FP_64 : Mips::FP, VT); 0
2523 return FrameAddr; 0
2524 } 0
2525 ----
2526 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerRETURNADDR(SDValue Op, 0
2527 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
2528 if (verifyReturnAddressArgumentIsConstant(Op, DAG)) 0
2529 return SDValue(); 0
2530 ----
2531 // check the depth ----
2532 if (cast(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue() != 0) { 0
2533 DAG.getContext()->emitError( 0
2534 "return address can be determined only for current frame"); ----
2535 return SDValue(); 0
2536 } ----
2537 ----
2538 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction(); 0
2539 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo(); 0
2540 MVT VT = Op.getSimpleValueType(); 0
2541 unsigned RA = ABI.IsN64() ? Mips::RA_64 : Mips::RA; 0
2542 MFI.setReturnAddressIsTaken(true); 0
2543 ----
2544 // Return RA, which contains the return address. Mark it an implicit live-in. ----
2545 Register Reg = MF.addLiveIn(RA, getRegClassFor(VT)); 0
2546 return DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), SDLoc(Op), Reg, VT); 0
2547 } ----
2548 ----
2549 // An EH_RETURN is the result of lowering llvm.eh.return which in turn is ----
2550 // generated from __builtin_eh_return (offset, handler) ----
2551 // The effect of this is to adjust the stack pointer by "offset" ----
2552 // and then branch to "handler". ----
2553 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerEH_RETURN(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) 0
2554 const { ----
2555 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction(); 0
2556 MipsFunctionInfo *MipsFI = MF.getInfo(); 0
2557 ----
2558 MipsFI->setCallsEhReturn(); 0
2559 SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0); 0
2560 SDValue Offset = Op.getOperand(1); 0
2561 SDValue Handler = Op.getOperand(2); 0
2562 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2563 EVT Ty = ABI.IsN64() ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32; 0
2564 ----
2565 // Store stack offset in V1, store jump target in V0. Glue CopyToReg and ----
2566 // EH_RETURN nodes, so that instructions are emitted back-to-back. ----
2567 unsigned OffsetReg = ABI.IsN64() ? Mips::V1_64 : Mips::V1; 0
2568 unsigned AddrReg = ABI.IsN64() ? Mips::V0_64 : Mips::V0; 0
2569 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, OffsetReg, Offset, SDValue()); 0
2570 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, AddrReg, Handler, Chain.getValue(1)); 0
2571 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::EH_RETURN, DL, MVT::Other, Chain, 0
2572 DAG.getRegister(OffsetReg, Ty), ----
2573 DAG.getRegister(AddrReg, getPointerTy(MF.getDataLayout())), 0
2574 Chain.getValue(1)); 0
2575 } 0

2577 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerATOMIC_FENCE(SDValue Op, 0
2578 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
2579 // FIXME: Need pseudo-fence for 'singlethread' fences ----
2580 // FIXME: Set SType for weaker fences where supported/appropriate. ----
2581 unsigned SType = 0; 0
2582 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2583 return DAG.getNode(MipsISD::Sync, DL, MVT::Other, Op.getOperand(0), 0
2584 DAG.getConstant(SType, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2585 } 0
2586 ----
2587 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerShiftLeftParts(SDValue Op, 0
2588 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
2589 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2590 MVT VT = Subtarget.isGP64bit() ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32; 0
2591 ----
2592 SDValue Lo = Op.getOperand(0), Hi = Op.getOperand(1); 0
2593 SDValue Shamt = Op.getOperand(2); 0
2594 // if shamt < (VT.bits): ----
2595 // lo = (shl lo, shamt) ----
2596 // hi = (or (shl hi, shamt) (srl (srl lo, 1), ~shamt)) ----
2597 // else: ----
2598 // lo = 0 ----
2599 // hi = (shl lo, shamt[4:0]) ----
2600 SDValue Not = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, MVT::i32, Shamt, 0
2601 DAG.getConstant(-1, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2602 SDValue ShiftRight1Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Lo, 0
2603 DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VT)); ----
2604 SDValue ShiftRightLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, ShiftRight1Lo, Not); 0
2605 SDValue ShiftLeftHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Hi, Shamt); 0
2606 SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShiftLeftHi, ShiftRightLo); 0
2607 SDValue ShiftLeftLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Lo, Shamt); 0
2608 SDValue Cond = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MVT::i32, Shamt, 0
2609 DAG.getConstant(VT.getSizeInBits(), DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2610 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, Cond, 0
2611 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), ShiftLeftLo); ----
2612 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, Cond, ShiftLeftLo, Or); 0
2613 ----
2614 SDValue Ops[2] = {Lo, Hi}; 0
2615 return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL); 0
2616 } 0
2617 ----
2618 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::lowerShiftRightParts(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
2619 bool IsSRA) const { ----
2620 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
2621 SDValue Lo = Op.getOperand(0), Hi = Op.getOperand(1); 0
2622 SDValue Shamt = Op.getOperand(2); 0
2623 MVT VT = Subtarget.isGP64bit() ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32; 0
2624 ----
2625 // if shamt < (VT.bits): ----
2626 // lo = (or (shl (shl hi, 1), ~shamt) (srl lo, shamt)) ----
2627 // if isSRA: ----
2628 // hi = (sra hi, shamt) ----
2629 // else: ----
2630 // hi = (srl hi, shamt) ----
2631 // else: ----
2632 // if isSRA: ----
2633 // lo = (sra hi, shamt[4:0]) ----
2634 // hi = (sra hi, 31) ----
2635 // else: ----
2636 // lo = (srl hi, shamt[4:0]) ----
2637 // hi = 0 ----
2638 SDValue Not = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, MVT::i32, Shamt, 0
2639 DAG.getConstant(-1, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2640 SDValue ShiftLeft1Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Hi, 0
2641 DAG.getConstant(1, DL, VT)); ----
2642 SDValue ShiftLeftHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, ShiftLeft1Hi, Not); 0
2643 SDValue ShiftRightLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Lo, Shamt); 0
2644 SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShiftLeftHi, ShiftRightLo); 0
2645 SDValue ShiftRightHi = DAG.getNode(IsSRA ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL, 0
2646 DL, VT, Hi, Shamt); ----
2647 SDValue Cond = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MVT::i32, Shamt, 0
2648 DAG.getConstant(VT.getSizeInBits(), DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2649 SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, VT, Hi, 0
2650 DAG.getConstant(VT.getSizeInBits() - 1, DL, VT)); 0
2651 ----
2652 if (!(Subtarget.hasMips4() || Subtarget.hasMips32())) { 0
2653 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(VT, VT); 0
2654 return DAG.getNode(Subtarget.isGP64bit() ? Mips::PseudoD_SELECT_I64 0
2655 : Mips::PseudoD_SELECT_I, ----
2656 DL, VTList, Cond, ShiftRightHi, ----
2657 IsSRA ? Ext : DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), Or, 0
2658 ShiftRightHi); 0
2659 } ----
2660 ----
2661 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, Cond, ShiftRightHi, Or); 0
2662 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, Cond, 0
2663 IsSRA ? Ext : DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), ShiftRightHi); 0
2664 ----
2665 SDValue Ops[2] = {Lo, Hi}; 0
2666 return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL); 0
2667 } 0

2670 SDValue Chain, SDValue Src, unsigned Offset) { ----
2671 SDValue Ptr = LD->getBasePtr(); 0
2672 EVT VT = LD->getValueType(0), MemVT = LD->getMemoryVT(); 0
2673 EVT BasePtrVT = Ptr.getValueType(); 0
2674 SDLoc DL(LD); 0
2675 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::Other); 0

2677 if (Offset) 0
2678 Ptr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, BasePtrVT, Ptr, 0
2679 DAG.getConstant(Offset, DL, BasePtrVT)); ----
2680 ----
2681 SDValue Ops[] = { Chain, Ptr, Src }; 0
2682 return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, VTList, Ops, MemVT, 0

2848 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2849 // Calling Convention Implementation ----
2850 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2851 ----
2852 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2853 // TODO: Implement a generic logic using tblgen that can support this. ----
2854 // Mips O32 ABI rules: ----
2855 // --- ----
2856 // i32 - Passed in A0, A1, A2, A3 and stack ----
2857 // f32 - Only passed in f32 registers if no int reg has been used yet to hold ----
2858 // an argument. Otherwise, passed in A1, A2, A3 and stack. ----
2859 // f64 - Only passed in two aliased f32 registers if no int reg has been used ----
2860 // yet to hold an argument. Otherwise, use A2, A3 and stack. If A1 is ----
2861 // not used, it must be shadowed. If only A3 is available, shadow it and ----
2862 // go to stack. ----
2863 // vXiX - Received as scalarized i32s, passed in A0 - A3 and the stack. ----
2864 // vXf32 - Passed in either a pair of registers {A0, A1}, {A2, A3} or {A0 - A3} ----
2865 // with the remainder spilled to the stack. ----
2866 // vXf64 - Passed in either {A0, A1, A2, A3} or {A2, A3} and in both cases ----
2867 // spilling the remainder to the stack. ----
2868 // ----
2869 // For vararg functions, all arguments are passed in A0, A1, A2, A3 and stack. ----
2870 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2871 ----
2872 static bool CC_MipsO32(unsigned ValNo, MVT ValVT, MVT LocVT, 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2873 CCValAssign::LocInfo LocInfo, ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags, ----
2874 CCState &State, ArrayRef F64Regs) { ----
2875 const MipsSubtarget &Subtarget = static_cast( ----
2876 State.getMachineFunction().getSubtarget()); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2877 ----
2878 static const MCPhysReg IntRegs[] = { Mips::A0, Mips::A1, Mips::A2, Mips::A3 }; ----
2879 ----
2880 const MipsCCState * MipsState = static_cast(&State); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2881 ----
2882 static const MCPhysReg F32Regs[] = { Mips::F12, Mips::F14 }; ----
2883 ----
2884 static const MCPhysReg FloatVectorIntRegs[] = { Mips::A0, Mips::A2 }; ----
2885 ----
2886 // Do not process byval args here. ----
2887 if (ArgFlags.isByVal()) 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2888 return true; 0
2889 ----
2890 // Promote i8 and i16 ----
2891 if (ArgFlags.isInReg() && !Subtarget.isLittle()) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2892 if (LocVT == MVT::i8 || LocVT == MVT::i16 || LocVT == MVT::i32) { 0

2898 else ----

2904 if (LocVT == MVT::i8 || LocVT == MVT::i16) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2905 LocVT = MVT::i32; 0
2906 if (ArgFlags.isSExt()) 0
2907 LocInfo = CCValAssign::SExt; 0
2908 else if (ArgFlags.isZExt()) 0
2909 LocInfo = CCValAssign::ZExt; 0
2910 else ----
2911 LocInfo = CCValAssign::AExt; 0
2912 } ----
2913 ----
2914 unsigned Reg; ----
2915 ----
2916 // f32 and f64 are allocated in A0, A1, A2, A3 when either of the following ----
2917 // is true: function is vararg, argument is 3rd or higher, there is previous ----
