2923 bool isVectorFloat = MipsState->WasOriginalArgVectorFloat(ValNo); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2924 ----
2925 // The MIPS vector ABI for floats passes them in a pair of registers ----
2926 if (ValVT == MVT::i32 && isVectorFloat) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2927 // This is the start of an vector that was scalarized into an unknown number ----
2928 // of components. It doesn't matter how many there are. Allocate one of the ----
2929 // notional 8 byte aligned registers which map onto the argument stack, and ----
2930 // shadow the register lost to alignment requirements. ----
2931 if (ArgFlags.isSplit()) { 0
2932 Reg = State.AllocateReg(FloatVectorIntRegs); 0
2933 if (Reg == Mips::A2) 0
2934 State.AllocateReg(Mips::A1); 0
2935 else if (Reg == 0) 0
2936 State.AllocateReg(Mips::A3); 0
2937 } else { ----
2938 // If we're an intermediate component of the split, we can just attempt to ----
2939 // allocate a register directly. ----
2940 Reg = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs); 0
2941 } ----
2942 } else if (ValVT == MVT::i32 || 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2943 (ValVT == MVT::f32 && AllocateFloatsInIntReg)) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2944 Reg = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

2946 // the allocated register must be either A0 or A2. ----
2947 if (isI64 && (Reg == Mips::A1 || Reg == Mips::A3)) 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2948 Reg = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs); 0

2950 } else if (ValVT == MVT::f64 && AllocateFloatsInIntReg) { 0

2953 // Allocate int register and shadow next int register. If first ----
2954 // available register is Mips::A1 or Mips::A3, shadow it too. ----
2955 Reg = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs); 0
2956 if (Reg == Mips::A1 || Reg == Mips::A3) 0
2957 Reg = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs); 0
2958 ----
2959 if (Reg) { 0

2964 State.addLoc( 0

2967 } ----
2968 } else if (ValVT.isFloatingPoint() && !AllocateFloatsInIntReg) { 0
2969 // we are guaranteed to find an available float register ----
2970 if (ValVT == MVT::f32) { 0
2971 Reg = State.AllocateReg(F32Regs); 0
2972 // Shadow int register ----
2973 State.AllocateReg(IntRegs); 0
2974 } else { ----
2975 Reg = State.AllocateReg(F64Regs); 0
2976 // Shadow int registers ----
2977 unsigned Reg2 = State.AllocateReg(IntRegs); 0
2978 if (Reg2 == Mips::A1 || Reg2 == Mips::A3) 0

2980 State.AllocateReg(IntRegs); 0
2981 } ----
2982 } else ----

2984 ----
2985 if (!Reg) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2986 unsigned Offset = State.AllocateStack(ValVT.getStoreSize(), OrigAlign); 0
2987 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, Offset, LocVT, LocInfo)); 0
2988 } else ----
2989 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo)); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2990 ----
2991 return false; 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2992 } ----

3026 ----
3027 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::passArgOnStack(SDValue StackPtr, unsigned Offset, 0

3030 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----

3032 SDValue PtrOff = ----
3033 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()), StackPtr, 0
3034 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(Offset, DL)); ----

3037 ----
3038 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo(); 0
3039 int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(Arg.getValueSizeInBits() / 8, Offset, false); 0
3040 SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0
3041 return DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, Arg, FIN, MachinePointerInfo(), MaybeAlign(), 0
3042 MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile); 0
3043 } ----
3044 ----
3045 void MipsTargetLowering:: 0
3046 getOpndList(SmallVectorImpl &Ops, ----
3047 std::deque> &RegsToPass, ----
3048 bool IsPICCall, bool GlobalOrExternal, bool InternalLinkage, ----
3049 bool IsCallReloc, CallLoweringInfo &CLI, SDValue Callee, ----
3050 SDValue Chain) const { ----
3051 // Insert node "GP copy globalreg" before call to function. ----
3052 // ----
3053 // R_MIPS_CALL* operators (emitted when non-internal functions are called ----
3054 // in PIC mode) allow symbols to be resolved via lazy binding. ----
3055 // The lazy binding stub requires GP to point to the GOT. ----
3056 // Note that we don't need GP to point to the GOT for indirect calls ----
3057 // (when R_MIPS_CALL* is not used for the call) because Mips linker generates ----
3058 // lazy binding stub for a function only when R_MIPS_CALL* are the only relocs ----
3059 // used for the function (that is, Mips linker doesn't generate lazy binding ----
3060 // stub for a function whose address is taken in the program). ----
3061 if (IsPICCall && !InternalLinkage && IsCallReloc) { 0
3062 unsigned GPReg = ABI.IsN64() ? Mips::GP_64 : Mips::GP; 0
3063 EVT Ty = ABI.IsN64() ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32; 0
3064 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(GPReg, getGlobalReg(CLI.DAG, Ty))); 0
3065 } ----
3066 ----
3067 // Build a sequence of copy-to-reg nodes chained together with token ----
3068 // chain and flag operands which copy the outgoing args into registers. ----
3069 // The InGlue in necessary since all emitted instructions must be ----
3070 // stuck together. ----
3071 SDValue InGlue; 0
3072 ----
3073 for (auto &R : RegsToPass) { 0
3074 Chain = CLI.DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, CLI.DL, R.first, R.second, InGlue); 0
3075 InGlue = Chain.getValue(1); 0
3076 } ----
3077 ----
3078 // Add argument registers to the end of the list so that they are ----
3079 // known live into the call. ----
3080 for (auto &R : RegsToPass) 0
3081 Ops.push_back(CLI.DAG.getRegister(R.first, R.second.getValueType())); 0
3082 ----
3083 // Add a register mask operand representing the call-preserved registers. ----
3084 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo(); 0
3085 const uint32_t *Mask = ----
3086 TRI->getCallPreservedMask(CLI.DAG.getMachineFunction(), CLI.CallConv); 0
3087 assert(Mask && "Missing call preserved mask for calling convention"); 0
3088 if (Subtarget.inMips16HardFloat()) { 0
3089 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast(CLI.Callee)) { 0
3090 StringRef Sym = G->getGlobal()->getName(); 0
3091 Function *F = G->getGlobal()->getParent()->getFunction(Sym); 0
3092 if (F && F->hasFnAttribute("__Mips16RetHelper")) { 0
3093 Mask = MipsRegisterInfo::getMips16RetHelperMask(); 0
3094 } ----
3095 } ----
3096 } ----
3097 Ops.push_back(CLI.DAG.getRegisterMask(Mask)); 0
3098 ----
3099 if (InGlue.getNode()) 0
3100 Ops.push_back(InGlue); 0
3101 } 0
3102 ----
3103 void MipsTargetLowering::AdjustInstrPostInstrSelection(MachineInstr &MI, 0
3104 SDNode *Node) const { ----
3105 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
3106 default: 0
3107 return; 0
3108 case Mips::JALR: 0
3109 case Mips::JALRPseudo: ----
3110 case Mips::JALR64: ----
3111 case Mips::JALR64Pseudo: ----
3112 case Mips::JALR16_MM: ----
3113 case Mips::JALRC16_MMR6: ----
3114 case Mips::TAILCALLREG: ----
3115 case Mips::TAILCALLREG64: ----
3116 case Mips::TAILCALLR6REG: ----
3117 case Mips::TAILCALL64R6REG: ----
3118 case Mips::TAILCALLREG_MM: ----
3119 case Mips::TAILCALLREG_MMR6: { ----
3120 if (!EmitJalrReloc || 0
3121 Subtarget.inMips16Mode() || 0
3122 !isPositionIndependent() || 0
3123 Node->getNumOperands() < 1 || 0
3124 Node->getOperand(0).getNumOperands() < 2) { 0
3125 return; 0
3126 } ----
3127 // We are after the callee address, set by LowerCall(). ----
3128 // If added to MI, asm printer will emit .reloc R_MIPS_JALR for the ----
3129 // symbol. ----
3130 const SDValue TargetAddr = Node->getOperand(0).getOperand(1); 0
3131 StringRef Sym; 0
3132 if (const GlobalAddressSDNode *G = 0
3133 dyn_cast_or_null(TargetAddr)) { 0
3134 // We must not emit the R_MIPS_JALR relocation against data symbols ----
3135 // since this will cause run-time crashes if the linker replaces the ----
3136 // call instruction with a relative branch to the data symbol. ----
3137 if (!isa(G->getGlobal())) { 0
3138 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Not adding R_MIPS_JALR against data symbol " 0
3139 << G->getGlobal()->getName() << "\n"); ----
3140 return; 0
3141 } ----
3142 Sym = G->getGlobal()->getName(); 0
3143 } ----
3144 else if (const ExternalSymbolSDNode *ES = 0
3145 dyn_cast_or_null(TargetAddr)) { 0
3146 Sym = ES->getSymbol(); 0
3147 } ----
3148 ----
3149 if (Sym.empty()) 0
3150 return; 0
3151 ----
3152 MachineFunction *MF = MI.getParent()->getParent(); 0
3153 MCSymbol *S = MF->getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Sym); 0
3154 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Adding R_MIPS_JALR against " << Sym << "\n"); 0
3155 MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateMCSymbol(S, MipsII::MO_JALR)); 0
3156 } ----
3157 } ----
3158 } ----

3160 /// LowerCall - functions arguments are copied from virtual regs to ----
3161 /// (physical regs)/(stack frame), CALLSEQ_START and CALLSEQ_END are emitted. ----
3162 SDValue ----
3163 MipsTargetLowering::LowerCall(TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo &CLI, 0
3164 SmallVectorImpl &InVals) const { ----
3165 SelectionDAG &DAG = CLI.DAG; 0
3166 SDLoc DL = CLI.DL; 0
3167 SmallVectorImpl &Outs = CLI.Outs; 0
3168 SmallVectorImpl &OutVals = CLI.OutVals; 0
3169 SmallVectorImpl &Ins = CLI.Ins; 0
3170 SDValue Chain = CLI.Chain; 0
3171 SDValue Callee = CLI.Callee; 0
3172 bool &IsTailCall = CLI.IsTailCall; 0
3173 CallingConv::ID CallConv = CLI.CallConv; 0
3174 bool IsVarArg = CLI.IsVarArg; 0
3175 ----
3176 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction(); 0
3177 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo(); 0
3178 const TargetFrameLowering *TFL = Subtarget.getFrameLowering(); 0
3179 MipsFunctionInfo *FuncInfo = MF.getInfo(); 0
3180 bool IsPIC = isPositionIndependent(); 0
3181 ----
3182 // Analyze operands of the call, assigning locations to each operand. ----
3183 SmallVector ArgLocs; 0
3184 MipsCCState CCInfo( ----
3185 CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), ArgLocs, *DAG.getContext(), 0
3186 MipsCCState::getSpecialCallingConvForCallee(Callee.getNode(), Subtarget)); 0
3187 ----
3188 const ExternalSymbolSDNode *ES = ----
3189 dyn_cast_or_null(Callee.getNode()); 0
3190 ----
3191 // There is one case where CALLSEQ_START..CALLSEQ_END can be nested, which ----
3192 // is during the lowering of a call with a byval argument which produces ----
3193 // a call to memcpy. For the O32 case, this causes the caller to allocate ----
3194 // stack space for the reserved argument area for the callee, then recursively ----
3195 // again for the memcpy call. In the NEWABI case, this doesn't occur as those ----
3196 // ABIs mandate that the callee allocates the reserved argument area. We do ----
3197 // still produce nested CALLSEQ_START..CALLSEQ_END with zero space though. ----
3198 // ----
3199 // If the callee has a byval argument and memcpy is used, we are mandated ----
3200 // to already have produced a reserved argument area for the callee for O32. ----
3201 // Therefore, the reserved argument area can be reused for both calls. ----
3202 // ----
3203 // Other cases of calling memcpy cannot have a chain with a CALLSEQ_START ----
3204 // present, as we have yet to hook that node onto the chain. ----
3205 // ----
3206 // Hence, the CALLSEQ_START and CALLSEQ_END nodes can be eliminated in this ----
3207 // case. GCC does a similar trick, in that wherever possible, it calculates ----
3208 // the maximum out going argument area (including the reserved area), and ----
3209 // preallocates the stack space on entrance to the caller. ----
3210 // ----
3211 // FIXME: We should do the same for efficiency and space. ----
3212 ----
3213 // Note: The check on the calling convention below must match ----
3214 // MipsABIInfo::GetCalleeAllocdArgSizeInBytes(). ----
3215 bool MemcpyInByVal = ES && 0
3216 StringRef(ES->getSymbol()) == StringRef("memcpy") && 0
3217 CallConv != CallingConv::Fast && 0
3218 Chain.getOpcode() == ISD::CALLSEQ_START; 0
3219 ----
3220 // Allocate the reserved argument area. It seems strange to do this from the ----
3221 // caller side but removing it breaks the frame size calculation. ----
3222 unsigned ReservedArgArea = ----
3223 MemcpyInByVal ? 0 : ABI.GetCalleeAllocdArgSizeInBytes(CallConv); 0
3224 CCInfo.AllocateStack(ReservedArgArea, Align(1)); 0
3225 ----
3226 CCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(Outs, CC_Mips, CLI.getArgs(), 0
3227 ES ? ES->getSymbol() : nullptr); 0
3228 ----
3229 // Get a count of how many bytes are to be pushed on the stack. ----
3230 unsigned StackSize = CCInfo.getStackSize(); 0
3231 ----
3232 // Call site info for function parameters tracking. ----
3233 MachineFunction::CallSiteInfo CSInfo; 0
3234 ----
3235 // Check if it's really possible to do a tail call. Restrict it to functions ----
3236 // that are part of this compilation unit. ----
3237 bool InternalLinkage = false; 0
3238 if (IsTailCall) { 0
3239 IsTailCall = isEligibleForTailCallOptimization( 0
3240 CCInfo, StackSize, *MF.getInfo()); 0
3241 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast(Callee)) { 0
3242 InternalLinkage = G->getGlobal()->hasInternalLinkage(); 0
3243 IsTailCall &= (InternalLinkage || G->getGlobal()->hasLocalLinkage() || 0
3244 G->getGlobal()->hasPrivateLinkage() || 0
3245 G->getGlobal()->hasHiddenVisibility() || 0
3246 G->getGlobal()->hasProtectedVisibility()); 0
3247 } ----
3248 } ----
3249 if (!IsTailCall && CLI.CB && CLI.CB->isMustTailCall()) 0
3250 report_fatal_error("failed to perform tail call elimination on a call " 0
3251 "site marked musttail"); ----
3252 ----
3253 if (IsTailCall) 0
3254 ++NumTailCalls; 0
3255 ----
3256 // Chain is the output chain of the last Load/Store or CopyToReg node. ----
3257 // ByValChain is the output chain of the last Memcpy node created for copying ----
3258 // byval arguments to the stack. ----
3259 unsigned StackAlignment = TFL->getStackAlignment(); 0
3260 StackSize = alignTo(StackSize, StackAlignment); 0
3261 ----
3262 if (!(IsTailCall || MemcpyInByVal)) 0
3263 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, StackSize, 0, DL); 0
3264 ----
3265 SDValue StackPtr = ----
3266 DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, ABI.IsN64() ? Mips::SP_64 : Mips::SP, 0
3267 getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0
3268 ----
3269 std::deque> RegsToPass; 0
3270 SmallVector MemOpChains; 0
3271 ----
3272 CCInfo.rewindByValRegsInfo(); 0
3273 ----
3274 // Walk the register/memloc assignments, inserting copies/loads. ----
3275 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(), OutIdx = 0; i != e; ++i, ++OutIdx) { 0
3276 SDValue Arg = OutVals[OutIdx]; 0
3277 CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i]; 0
3278 MVT ValVT = VA.getValVT(), LocVT = VA.getLocVT(); 0
3279 ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[OutIdx].Flags; 0
3280 bool UseUpperBits = false; 0
3281 ----
3282 // ByVal Arg. ----
3283 if (Flags.isByVal()) { 0
3284 unsigned FirstByValReg, LastByValReg; ----
3285 unsigned ByValIdx = CCInfo.getInRegsParamsProcessed(); 0
3286 CCInfo.getInRegsParamInfo(ByValIdx, FirstByValReg, LastByValReg); 0
3287 ----
3288 assert(Flags.getByValSize() && 0
3289 "ByVal args of size 0 should have been ignored by front-end."); ----
3290 assert(ByValIdx < CCInfo.getInRegsParamsCount()); 0
3291 assert(!IsTailCall && 0
3292 "Do not tail-call optimize if there is a byval argument."); ----
3293 passByValArg(Chain, DL, RegsToPass, MemOpChains, StackPtr, MFI, DAG, Arg, 0
3294 FirstByValReg, LastByValReg, Flags, Subtarget.isLittle(), 0
3295 VA); ----
3296 CCInfo.nextInRegsParam(); 0
3297 continue; 0
3298 } 0
3299 ----
3300 // Promote the value if needed. ----
3301 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) { 0
3302 default: 0
3303 llvm_unreachable("Unknown loc info!"); 0
3304 case CCValAssign::Full: 0
3305 if (VA.isRegLoc()) { 0
3306 if ((ValVT == MVT::f32 && LocVT == MVT::i32) || 0
3307 (ValVT == MVT::f64 && LocVT == MVT::i64) || 0
3308 (ValVT == MVT::i64 && LocVT == MVT::f64)) 0
3309 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, LocVT, Arg); 0
3310 else if (ValVT == MVT::f64 && LocVT == MVT::i32) { 0
3311 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, 0
3312 Arg, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
3313 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::ExtractElementF64, DL, MVT::i32, 0
3314 Arg, DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
3315 if (!Subtarget.isLittle()) 0
3316 std::swap(Lo, Hi); 0
3317 ----
3318 assert(VA.needsCustom()); 0
3319 ----
3320 Register LocRegLo = VA.getLocReg(); 0
3321 Register LocRegHigh = ArgLocs[++i].getLocReg(); 0
3322 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(LocRegLo, Lo)); 0
3323 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(LocRegHigh, Hi)); 0
3324 continue; 0
3325 } 0
3326 } ----
3327 break; 0
3328 case CCValAssign::BCvt: 0
3329 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, LocVT, Arg); 0
3330 break; 0
3331 case CCValAssign::SExtUpper: 0
3332 UseUpperBits = true; 0
3333 [[fallthrough]]; ----
3334 case CCValAssign::SExt: 0
3335 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, LocVT, Arg); 0
3336 break; 0
3337 case CCValAssign::ZExtUpper: 0
3338 UseUpperBits = true; 0
3339 [[fallthrough]]; ----
3340 case CCValAssign::ZExt: 0
3341 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, LocVT, Arg); 0
3342 break; 0
3343 case CCValAssign::AExtUpper: 0
3344 UseUpperBits = true; 0
3345 [[fallthrough]]; ----
3346 case CCValAssign::AExt: 0
3347 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, LocVT, Arg); 0
3348 break; 0
3349 } ----
3350 ----
3351 if (UseUpperBits) { 0
3352 unsigned ValSizeInBits = Outs[OutIdx].ArgVT.getSizeInBits(); 0
3353 unsigned LocSizeInBits = VA.getLocVT().getSizeInBits(); 0
3354 Arg = DAG.getNode( 0
3355 ISD::SHL, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Arg, ----
3356 DAG.getConstant(LocSizeInBits - ValSizeInBits, DL, VA.getLocVT())); 0
3357 } ----
3358 ----
3359 // Arguments that can be passed on register must be kept at ----
3360 // RegsToPass vector ----
3361 if (VA.isRegLoc()) { 0
3362 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(VA.getLocReg(), Arg)); 0
3363 ----
3364 // If the parameter is passed through reg $D, which splits into ----
3365 // two physical registers, avoid creating call site info. ----
3366 if (Mips::AFGR64RegClass.contains(VA.getLocReg())) 0
3367 continue; 0
3368 ----
3369 // Collect CSInfo about which register passes which parameter. ----
3370 const TargetOptions &Options = DAG.getTarget().Options; 0
3371 if (Options.SupportsDebugEntryValues) 0
3372 CSInfo.emplace_back(VA.getLocReg(), i); 0
3373 ----
3374 continue; 0
3375 } 0
3376 ----
3377 // Register can't get to this point... ----
3378 assert(VA.isMemLoc()); 0
3379 ----
3380 // emit ISD::STORE whichs stores the ----
3381 // parameter value to a stack Location ----
3382 MemOpChains.push_back(passArgOnStack(StackPtr, VA.getLocMemOffset(), 0
3383 Chain, Arg, DL, IsTailCall, DAG)); 0
3384 } ----
3385 ----
3386 // Transform all store nodes into one single node because all store ----
3387 // nodes are independent of each other. ----
3388 if (!MemOpChains.empty()) 0
3389 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, MemOpChains); 0
3390 ----
3391 // If the callee is a GlobalAddress/ExternalSymbol node (quite common, every ----
3392 // direct call is) turn it into a TargetGlobalAddress/TargetExternalSymbol ----
3393 // node so that legalize doesn't hack it. ----
3394 ----
3395 EVT Ty = Callee.getValueType(); 0
3396 bool GlobalOrExternal = false, IsCallReloc = false; 0
3397 ----
3398 // The long-calls feature is ignored in case of PIC. ----
3399 // While we do not support -mshared / -mno-shared properly, ----
3400 // ignore long-calls in case of -mabicalls too. ----
3401 if (!Subtarget.isABICalls() && !IsPIC) { 0
3402 // If the function should be called using "long call", ----
3403 // get its address into a register to prevent using ----
3404 // of the `jal` instruction for the direct call. ----
3405 if (auto *N = dyn_cast(Callee)) { 0
3406 if (Subtarget.useLongCalls()) 0
3407 Callee = Subtarget.hasSym32() 0
3408 ? getAddrNonPIC(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG) 0
3409 : getAddrNonPICSym64(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG); 0
3410 } else if (auto *N = dyn_cast(Callee)) { 0
3411 bool UseLongCalls = Subtarget.useLongCalls(); 0
3412 // If the function has long-call/far/near attribute ----
3413 // it overrides command line switch pased to the backend. ----
3414 if (auto *F = dyn_cast(N->getGlobal())) { 0
3415 if (F->hasFnAttribute("long-call")) 0
3416 UseLongCalls = true; 0
3417 else if (F->hasFnAttribute("short-call")) 0
3418 UseLongCalls = false; 0
3419 } ----
3420 if (UseLongCalls) 0
3421 Callee = Subtarget.hasSym32() 0
3422 ? getAddrNonPIC(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG) 0
3423 : getAddrNonPICSym64(N, SDLoc(N), Ty, DAG); 0
3424 } ----
3425 } ----
3426 ----
3427 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast(Callee)) { 0
3428 if (IsPIC) { 0
3429 const GlobalValue *Val = G->getGlobal(); 0
3430 InternalLinkage = Val->hasInternalLinkage(); 0
3431 ----
3432 if (InternalLinkage) 0
3433 Callee = getAddrLocal(G, DL, Ty, DAG, ABI.IsN32() || ABI.IsN64()); 0
3434 else if (Subtarget.useXGOT()) { 0
3435 Callee = getAddrGlobalLargeGOT(G, DL, Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_CALL_HI16, 0
3436 MipsII::MO_CALL_LO16, Chain, ----
3437 FuncInfo->callPtrInfo(MF, Val)); 0
3438 IsCallReloc = true; 0
3439 } else { ----
3440 Callee = getAddrGlobal(G, DL, Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_GOT_CALL, Chain, 0
3441 FuncInfo->callPtrInfo(MF, Val)); 0
3442 IsCallReloc = true; 0
3443 } ----
3444 } else ----
3445 Callee = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(G->getGlobal(), DL, 0
3446 getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()), 0, 0
3447 MipsII::MO_NO_FLAG); ----
3448 GlobalOrExternal = true; 0
3449 } ----
3450 else if (ExternalSymbolSDNode *S = dyn_cast(Callee)) { 0
3451 const char *Sym = S->getSymbol(); 0
3452 ----
3453 if (!IsPIC) // static 0
3454 Callee = DAG.getTargetExternalSymbol( 0
3455 Sym, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()), MipsII::MO_NO_FLAG); 0
3456 else if (Subtarget.useXGOT()) { 0
3457 Callee = getAddrGlobalLargeGOT(S, DL, Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_CALL_HI16, 0
3458 MipsII::MO_CALL_LO16, Chain, ----
3459 FuncInfo->callPtrInfo(MF, Sym)); 0
3460 IsCallReloc = true; 0
3461 } else { // PIC ----
3462 Callee = getAddrGlobal(S, DL, Ty, DAG, MipsII::MO_GOT_CALL, Chain, 0
3463 FuncInfo->callPtrInfo(MF, Sym)); 0
3464 IsCallReloc = true; 0
3465 } ----
3466 ----
3467 GlobalOrExternal = true; 0
3468 } ----
3469 ----
3470 SmallVector Ops(1, Chain); 0
3471 SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue); 0
3472 ----
3473 getOpndList(Ops, RegsToPass, IsPIC, GlobalOrExternal, InternalLinkage, 0
3474 IsCallReloc, CLI, Callee, Chain); ----
3475 ----
3476 if (IsTailCall) { 0
3477 MF.getFrameInfo().setHasTailCall(); 0
3478 SDValue Ret = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::TailCall, DL, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
3479 DAG.addCallSiteInfo(Ret.getNode(), std::move(CSInfo)); 0
3480 return Ret; 0
3481 } ----
3482 ----
3483 Chain = DAG.getNode(MipsISD::JmpLink, DL, NodeTys, Ops); 0
3484 SDValue InGlue = Chain.getValue(1); 0
3485 ----
3486 DAG.addCallSiteInfo(Chain.getNode(), std::move(CSInfo)); 0
3487 ----
3488 // Create the CALLSEQ_END node in the case of where it is not a call to ----
3489 // memcpy. ----
3490 if (!(MemcpyInByVal)) { 0
3491 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, StackSize, 0, InGlue, DL); 0
3492 InGlue = Chain.getValue(1); 0
3493 } ----
3494 ----
3495 // Handle result values, copying them out of physregs into vregs that we ----
3496 // return. ----
3497 return LowerCallResult(Chain, InGlue, CallConv, IsVarArg, Ins, DL, DAG, 0
3498 InVals, CLI); 0
3499 } 0
3500 ----
3501 /// LowerCallResult - Lower the result values of a call into the ----
3502 /// appropriate copies out of appropriate physical registers. ----
3503 SDValue MipsTargetLowering::LowerCallResult( 0
3504 SDValue Chain, SDValue InGlue, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool IsVarArg, ----
3505 const SmallVectorImpl &Ins, const SDLoc &DL, ----
3506 SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl &InVals, ----
3507 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo &CLI) const { ----
3508 // Assign locations to each value returned by this call. ----
3509 SmallVector RVLocs; 0
3510 MipsCCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs, ----
3511 *DAG.getContext()); 0
3512 ----
3513 const ExternalSymbolSDNode *ES = ----
3514 dyn_cast_or_null(CLI.Callee.getNode()); 0
3515 CCInfo.AnalyzeCallResult(Ins, RetCC_Mips, CLI.RetTy, 0
3516 ES ? ES->getSymbol() : nullptr); 0
3517 ----
3518 // Copy all of the result registers out of their specified physreg. ----
3519 for (unsigned i = 0; i != RVLocs.size(); ++i) { 0
3520 CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i]; 0
3521 assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Can only return in registers!"); 0
3522 ----
3523 SDValue Val = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, RVLocs[i].getLocReg(), 0
3524 RVLocs[i].getLocVT(), InGlue); 0
3525 Chain = Val.getValue(1); 0
3526 InGlue = Val.getValue(2); 0
3527 ----
3528 if (VA.isUpperBitsInLoc()) { 0
3529 unsigned ValSizeInBits = Ins[i].ArgVT.getSizeInBits(); 0
3530 unsigned LocSizeInBits = VA.getLocVT().getSizeInBits(); 0
3531 unsigned Shift = ----
3532 VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::ZExtUpper ? ISD::SRL : ISD::SRA; 0
3533 Val = DAG.getNode( 0
3534 Shift, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val, ----
3535 DAG.getConstant(LocSizeInBits - ValSizeInBits, DL, VA.getLocVT())); 0
3536 } ----
3537 ----
3538 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) { 0
3539 default: 0
3540 llvm_unreachable("Unknown loc info!"); 0
3541 case CCValAssign::Full: 0
3542 break; 0
3543 case CCValAssign::BCvt: 0
3544 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VA.getValVT(), Val); 0
3545 break; 0
3546 case CCValAssign::AExt: 0
3547 case CCValAssign::AExtUpper: ----
3548 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VA.getValVT(), Val); 0
3549 break; 0
3550 case CCValAssign::ZExt: 0
3551 case CCValAssign::ZExtUpper: ----
3552 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val, 0
3553 DAG.getValueType(VA.getValVT())); ----

3932 ----
3933 /// getConstraintType - Given a constraint letter, return the type of ----
3934 /// constraint it is for this target. ----
3935 MipsTargetLowering::ConstraintType ----
3936 MipsTargetLowering::getConstraintType(StringRef Constraint) const { 0
3937 // Mips specific constraints ----
3938 // GCC config/mips/constraints.md ----
3939 // ----
3940 // 'd' : An address register. Equivalent to r ----
3941 // unless generating MIPS16 code. ----
3942 // 'y' : Equivalent to r; retained for ----
3943 // backwards compatibility. ----
3944 // 'c' : A register suitable for use in an indirect ----
3945 // jump. This will always be $25 for -mabicalls. ----
3946 // 'l' : The lo register. 1 word storage. ----
3947 // 'x' : The hilo register pair. Double word storage. ----
3948 if (Constraint.size() == 1) { 0
3949 switch (Constraint[0]) { 0
3950 default : break; 0
3951 case 'd': 0
3952 case 'y': ----
3953 case 'f': ----
3954 case 'c': ----
3955 case 'l': ----
3956 case 'x': ----
3957 return C_RegisterClass; 0
3958 case 'R': 0
3959 return C_Memory; 0
3960 } ----
3961 } ----
3962 ----
3963 if (Constraint == "ZC") 0
3964 return C_Memory; 0
3965 ----
3966 return TargetLowering::getConstraintType(Constraint); 0
3967 } ----
3968 ----
3969 /// Examine constraint type and operand type and determine a weight value. ----
3970 /// This object must already have been set up with the operand type ----
3971 /// and the current alternative constraint selected. ----
3972 TargetLowering::ConstraintWeight ----
3973 MipsTargetLowering::getSingleConstraintMatchWeight( 0
3974 AsmOperandInfo &info, const char *constraint) const { ----
3975 ConstraintWeight weight = CW_Invalid; 0
3976 Value *CallOperandVal = info.CallOperandVal; 0
3977 // If we don't have a value, we can't do a match, ----
3978 // but allow it at the lowest weight. ----
3979 if (!CallOperandVal) 0
3980 return CW_Default; 0
3981 Type *type = CallOperandVal->getType(); 0
3982 // Look at the constraint type. ----
3983 switch (*constraint) { 0
3984 default: 0
3985 weight = TargetLowering::getSingleConstraintMatchWeight(info, constraint); 0
3986 break; 0
3987 case 'd': 0
3988 case 'y': ----
3989 if (type->isIntegerTy()) 0
3990 weight = CW_Register; 0
3991 break; 0
3992 case 'f': // FPU or MSA register 0
3993 if (Subtarget.hasMSA() && type->isVectorTy() && 0
3994 type->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getFixedValue() == 128) 0
3995 weight = CW_Register; 0
3996 else if (type->isFloatTy()) 0
3997 weight = CW_Register; 0
3998 break; 0
3999 case 'c': // $25 for indirect jumps 0
4000 case 'l': // lo register ----
4001 case 'x': // hilo register pair ----
4002 if (type->isIntegerTy()) 0
4003 weight = CW_SpecificReg; 0
4004 break; 0
4005 case 'I': // signed 16 bit immediate 0
4006 case 'J': // integer zero ----
4007 case 'K': // unsigned 16 bit immediate ----
4008 case 'L': // signed 32 bit immediate where lower 16 bits are 0 ----
4009 case 'N': // immediate in the range of -65535 to -1 (inclusive) ----
4010 case 'O': // signed 15 bit immediate (+- 16383) ----
4011 case 'P': // immediate in the range of 65535 to 1 (inclusive) ----
4012 if (isa(CallOperandVal)) 0
4013 weight = CW_Constant; 0
4014 break; 0
4015 case 'R': 0
4016 weight = CW_Memory; 0
4017 break; 0
4018 } ----
4019 return weight; 0
4020 } ----
4021 ----
4022 /// This is a helper function to parse a physical register string and split it ----
4023 /// into non-numeric and numeric parts (Prefix and Reg). The first boolean flag ----
4024 /// that is returned indicates whether parsing was successful. The second flag ----
4025 /// is true if the numeric part exists. ----
4026 static std::pair parsePhysicalReg(StringRef C, StringRef &Prefix, 0
4027 unsigned long long &Reg) { ----
4028 if (C.front() != '{' || C.back() != '}') 0
4029 return std::make_pair(false, false); 0
4030 ----
4031 // Search for the first numeric character. ----
4032 StringRef::const_iterator I, B = C.begin() + 1, E = C.end() - 1; 0
4033 I = std::find_if(B, E, isdigit); 0
4034 ----
4035 Prefix = StringRef(B, I - B); 0
4036 ----
4037 // The second flag is set to false if no numeric characters were found. ----
4038 if (I == E) 0
4039 return std::make_pair(true, false); 0
4040 ----
4041 // Parse the numeric characters. ----
4042 return std::make_pair(!getAsUnsignedInteger(StringRef(I, E - I), 10, Reg), 0
4043 true); 0
4044 } ----
4045 ----
4046 EVT MipsTargetLowering::getTypeForExtReturn(LLVMContext &Context, EVT VT, 0
4047 ISD::NodeType) const { ----
4048 bool Cond = !Subtarget.isABI_O32() && VT.getSizeInBits() == 32; 0
4049 EVT MinVT = getRegisterType(Cond ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32); 0
4050 return VT.bitsLT(MinVT) ? MinVT : VT; 0
4051 } ----
4052 ----
4053 std::pair MipsTargetLowering:: 0
4054 parseRegForInlineAsmConstraint(StringRef C, MVT VT) const { ----
4055 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = ----
4056 Subtarget.getRegisterInfo(); 0
4057 const TargetRegisterClass *RC; ----
4058 StringRef Prefix; 0
4059 unsigned long long Reg; ----
4060 ----
4061 std::pair R = parsePhysicalReg(C, Prefix, Reg); 0
4062 ----
4063 if (!R.first) 0
4064 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr); 0
4065 ----
4066 if ((Prefix == "hi" || Prefix == "lo")) { // Parse hi/lo. 0
4067 // No numeric characters follow "hi" or "lo". ----
4068 if (R.second) 0
4069 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr); 0
4070 ----
4071 RC = TRI->getRegClass(Prefix == "hi" ? 0
4072 Mips::HI32RegClassID : Mips::LO32RegClassID); ----
4073 return std::make_pair(*(RC->begin()), RC); 0
4074 } else if (Prefix.startswith("$msa")) { 0
4075 // Parse $msa(ir|csr|access|save|modify|request|map|unmap) ----
4076 ----
4077 // No numeric characters follow the name. ----
4078 if (R.second) 0
4079 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr); 0
4080 ----
4081 Reg = StringSwitch(Prefix) 0
4082 .Case("$msair", Mips::MSAIR) 0
4083 .Case("$msacsr", Mips::MSACSR) 0
4084 .Case("$msaaccess", Mips::MSAAccess) 0
4085 .Case("$msasave", Mips::MSASave) 0
4086 .Case("$msamodify", Mips::MSAModify) 0
4087 .Case("$msarequest", Mips::MSARequest) 0
4088 .Case("$msamap", Mips::MSAMap) 0
4089 .Case("$msaunmap", Mips::MSAUnmap) 0
4090 .Default(0); 0
4091 ----
4092 if (!Reg) 0
4093 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr); 0
4094 ----
4095 RC = TRI->getRegClass(Mips::MSACtrlRegClassID); 0
4096 return std::make_pair(Reg, RC); 0
4097 } ----
4098 ----
4099 if (!R.second) 0
4100 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr); 0
4101 ----
4102 if (Prefix == "$f") { // Parse $f0-$f31. 0
4103 // If the size of FP registers is 64-bit or Reg is an even number, select ----
4104 // the 64-bit register class. Otherwise, select the 32-bit register class. ----
4105 if (VT == MVT::Other) 0
4106 VT = (Subtarget.isFP64bit() || !(Reg % 2)) ? MVT::f64 : MVT::f32; 0
4107 ----
4108 RC = getRegClassFor(VT); 0
4109 ----
4110 if (RC == &Mips::AFGR64RegClass) { 0
4111 assert(Reg % 2 == 0); 0
4112 Reg >>= 1; 0
4113 } ----
4114 } else if (Prefix == "$fcc") // Parse $fcc0-$fcc7. 0
4115 RC = TRI->getRegClass(Mips::FCCRegClassID); 0
4116 else if (Prefix == "$w") { // Parse $w0-$w31. 0
4117 RC = getRegClassFor((VT == MVT::Other) ? MVT::v16i8 : VT); 0
4118 } else { // Parse $0-$31. ----
4119 assert(Prefix == "$"); 0
4120 RC = getRegClassFor((VT == MVT::Other) ? MVT::i32 : VT); 0
4121 } ----
4122 ----
4123 assert(Reg < RC->getNumRegs()); 0
4124 return std::make_pair(*(RC->begin() + Reg), RC); 0
4125 } ----
4126 ----
4127 /// Given a register class constraint, like 'r', if this corresponds directly ----
4128 /// to an LLVM register class, return a register of 0 and the register class ----
4129 /// pointer. ----
4130 std::pair ----
4131 MipsTargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, 0
4132 StringRef Constraint, ----
4133 MVT VT) const { ----
4134 if (Constraint.size() == 1) { 0
4135 switch (Constraint[0]) { 0
4136 case 'd': // Address register. Same as 'r' unless generating MIPS16 code. 0
4137 case 'y': // Same as 'r'. Exists for compatibility. ----
4138 case 'r': ----
4139 if (VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i16 || VT == MVT::i8 || VT == MVT::i1) { 0
4140 if (Subtarget.inMips16Mode()) 0
4141 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::CPU16RegsRegClass); 0
4142 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4143 } ----
4144 if (VT == MVT::i64 && !Subtarget.isGP64bit()) 0
4145 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4146 if (VT == MVT::i64 && Subtarget.isGP64bit()) 0
4147 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::GPR64RegClass); 0
4148 // This will generate an error message ----
4149 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr); 0
4150 case 'f': // FPU or MSA register 0
4151 if (VT == MVT::v16i8) 0
4152 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::MSA128BRegClass); 0
4153 else if (VT == MVT::v8i16 || VT == MVT::v8f16) 0
4154 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::MSA128HRegClass); 0
4155 else if (VT == MVT::v4i32 || VT == MVT::v4f32) 0
4156 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::MSA128WRegClass); 0
4157 else if (VT == MVT::v2i64 || VT == MVT::v2f64) 0
4158 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::MSA128DRegClass); 0
4159 else if (VT == MVT::f32) 0
4160 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::FGR32RegClass); 0
4161 else if ((VT == MVT::f64) && (!Subtarget.isSingleFloat())) { 0
4162 if (Subtarget.isFP64bit()) 0
4163 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::FGR64RegClass); 0
4164 return std::make_pair(0U, &Mips::AFGR64RegClass); 0
4165 } ----
4166 break; 0
4167 case 'c': // register suitable for indirect jump 0
4168 if (VT == MVT::i32) 0
4169 return std::make_pair((unsigned)Mips::T9, &Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4170 if (VT == MVT::i64) 0
4171 return std::make_pair((unsigned)Mips::T9_64, &Mips::GPR64RegClass); 0
4172 // This will generate an error message ----
4173 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr); 0
4174 case 'l': // use the `lo` register to store values 0
4175 // that are no bigger than a word ----
4176 if (VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i16 || VT == MVT::i8) 0
4177 return std::make_pair((unsigned)Mips::LO0, &Mips::LO32RegClass); 0
4178 return std::make_pair((unsigned)Mips::LO0_64, &Mips::LO64RegClass); 0
4179 case 'x': // use the concatenated `hi` and `lo` registers 0
4180 // to store doubleword values ----
4181 // Fixme: Not triggering the use of both hi and low ----
4182 // This will generate an error message ----
4183 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr); 0
4184 } ----
4185 } ----
4186 ----
4187 if (!Constraint.empty()) { 0
4188 std::pair R; 0
4189 R = parseRegForInlineAsmConstraint(Constraint, VT); 0
4190 ----
4191 if (R.second) 0
4192 return R; 0
4193 } ----
4194 ----
4195 return TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, Constraint, VT); 0
4196 } ----
4197 ----
4198 /// LowerAsmOperandForConstraint - Lower the specified operand into the Ops ----
4199 /// vector. If it is invalid, don't add anything to Ops. ----
4200 void MipsTargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(SDValue Op, 0
4201 std::string &Constraint, ----
4202 std::vector&Ops, ----
4203 SelectionDAG &DAG) const { ----
4204 SDLoc DL(Op); 0
4205 SDValue Result; 0
4206 ----
4207 // Only support length 1 constraints for now. ----
4208 if (Constraint.length() > 1) return; 0
4209 ----
4210 char ConstraintLetter = Constraint[0]; 0
4211 switch (ConstraintLetter) { 0
4212 default: break; // This will fall through to the generic implementation 0
4213 case 'I': // Signed 16 bit constant 0
4214 // If this fails, the parent routine will give an error ----
4215 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Op)) { 0
4216 EVT Type = Op.getValueType(); 0
4217 int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue(); 0
4218 if (isInt<16>(Val)) { 0
4219 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type); 0
4220 break; 0
4221 } ----
4222 } ----
4223 return; 0
4224 case 'J': // integer zero 0
4225 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Op)) { 0
4226 EVT Type = Op.getValueType(); 0
4227 int64_t Val = C->getZExtValue(); 0
4228 if (Val == 0) { 0
4229 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, Type); 0
4230 break; 0
4231 } ----
4232 } ----
4233 return; 0
4234 case 'K': // unsigned 16 bit immediate 0
4235 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Op)) { 0
4236 EVT Type = Op.getValueType(); 0
4237 uint64_t Val = (uint64_t)C->getZExtValue(); 0
4238 if (isUInt<16>(Val)) { 0
4239 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type); 0
4240 break; 0
4241 } ----
4242 } ----
4243 return; 0
4244 case 'L': // signed 32 bit immediate where lower 16 bits are 0 0
4245 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Op)) { 0
4246 EVT Type = Op.getValueType(); 0
4247 int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue(); 0
4248 if ((isInt<32>(Val)) && ((Val & 0xffff) == 0)){ 0
4249 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type); 0
4250 break; 0
4251 } ----
4252 } ----
4253 return; 0
4254 case 'N': // immediate in the range of -65535 to -1 (inclusive) 0
4255 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Op)) { 0
4256 EVT Type = Op.getValueType(); 0
4257 int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue(); 0
4258 if ((Val >= -65535) && (Val <= -1)) { 0
4259 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type); 0
4260 break; 0
4261 } ----
4262 } ----
4263 return; 0
4264 case 'O': // signed 15 bit immediate 0
4265 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Op)) { 0
4266 EVT Type = Op.getValueType(); 0
4267 int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue(); 0
4268 if ((isInt<15>(Val))) { 0
4269 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type); 0
4270 break; 0
4271 } ----
4272 } ----
4273 return; 0
4274 case 'P': // immediate in the range of 1 to 65535 (inclusive) 0
4275 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Op)) { 0
4276 EVT Type = Op.getValueType(); 0
4277 int64_t Val = C->getSExtValue(); 0
4278 if ((Val <= 65535) && (Val >= 1)) { 0
4279 Result = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, Type); 0
4280 break; 0
4281 } ----
4282 } ----
4283 return; 0
4284 } ----
4285 ----
4286 if (Result.getNode()) { 0
4287 Ops.push_back(Result); 0
4288 return; 0
4289 } ----
4290 ----
4291 TargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(Op, Constraint, Ops, DAG); 0
4292 } 0
4293 ----
4294 bool MipsTargetLowering::isLegalAddressingMode(const DataLayout &DL, 0
4295 const AddrMode &AM, Type *Ty, ----
4296 unsigned AS, ----
4297 Instruction *I) const { ----
4298 // No global is ever allowed as a base. ----
4299 if (AM.BaseGV) 0
4300 return false; 0
4301 ----
4302 switch (AM.Scale) { 0
4303 case 0: // "r+i" or just "i", depending on HasBaseReg. 0
4304 break; 0
4305 case 1: 0
4306 if (!AM.HasBaseReg) // allow "r+i". 0
4307 break; 0
4308 return false; // disallow "r+r" or "r+r+i". 0
4309 default: 0
4310 return false; 0
4311 } ----
4312 ----
4313 return true; 0
4314 } ----

4319 return false; 0
4320 } ----

4324 if (Subtarget.hasMips64()) 0

4327 return MVT::i32; 0

4351 ----
4352 void MipsTargetLowering::copyByValRegs( 0
4353 SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &DL, std::vector &OutChains, ----
4354 SelectionDAG &DAG, const ISD::ArgFlagsTy &Flags, ----
4355 SmallVectorImpl &InVals, const Argument *FuncArg, ----
4356 unsigned FirstReg, unsigned LastReg, const CCValAssign &VA, ----
4357 MipsCCState &State) const { ----
4358 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction(); 0
4359 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo(); 0
4360 unsigned GPRSizeInBytes = Subtarget.getGPRSizeInBytes(); 0
4361 unsigned NumRegs = LastReg - FirstReg; 0
4362 unsigned RegAreaSize = NumRegs * GPRSizeInBytes; 0
4363 unsigned FrameObjSize = std::max(Flags.getByValSize(), RegAreaSize); 0
4364 int FrameObjOffset; ----
4365 ArrayRef ByValArgRegs = ABI.GetByValArgRegs(); 0
4366 ----
4367 if (RegAreaSize) 0
4368 FrameObjOffset = 0
4369 (int)ABI.GetCalleeAllocdArgSizeInBytes(State.getCallingConv()) - 0
4370 (int)((ByValArgRegs.size() - FirstReg) * GPRSizeInBytes); 0
4371 else ----
4372 FrameObjOffset = VA.getLocMemOffset(); 0
4373 ----
4374 // Create frame object. ----
4375 EVT PtrTy = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()); 0
4376 // Make the fixed object stored to mutable so that the load instructions ----
4377 // referencing it have their memory dependencies added. ----
4378 // Set the frame object as isAliased which clears the underlying objects ----
4379 // vector in ScheduleDAGInstrs::buildSchedGraph() resulting in addition of all ----
4380 // stores as dependencies for loads referencing this fixed object. ----
4381 int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(FrameObjSize, FrameObjOffset, false, true); 0
4382 SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, PtrTy); 0
4383 InVals.push_back(FIN); 0
4384 ----
4385 if (!NumRegs) 0
4386 return; 0
4387 ----
4388 // Copy arg registers. ----
4389 MVT RegTy = MVT::getIntegerVT(GPRSizeInBytes * 8); 0
4390 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(RegTy); 0
4391 ----
4392 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumRegs; ++I) { 0
4393 unsigned ArgReg = ByValArgRegs[FirstReg + I]; 0
4394 unsigned VReg = addLiveIn(MF, ArgReg, RC); 0
4395 unsigned Offset = I * GPRSizeInBytes; 0
4396 SDValue StorePtr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrTy, FIN, 0
4397 DAG.getConstant(Offset, DL, PtrTy)); ----
4398 SDValue Store = DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, DAG.getRegister(VReg, RegTy), 0
4399 StorePtr, MachinePointerInfo(FuncArg, Offset)); ----
4400 OutChains.push_back(Store); 0
4401 } ----
4402 } ----
4403 ----
4404 // Copy byVal arg to registers and stack. ----
4405 void MipsTargetLowering::passByValArg( 0
4406 SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &DL, ----
4407 std::deque> &RegsToPass, ----
4408 SmallVectorImpl &MemOpChains, SDValue StackPtr, ----
4409 MachineFrameInfo &MFI, SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Arg, unsigned FirstReg, ----
4410 unsigned LastReg, const ISD::ArgFlagsTy &Flags, bool isLittle, ----
4411 const CCValAssign &VA) const { ----
4412 unsigned ByValSizeInBytes = Flags.getByValSize(); 0
4413 unsigned OffsetInBytes = 0; // From beginning of struct 0
4414 unsigned RegSizeInBytes = Subtarget.getGPRSizeInBytes(); 0
4415 Align Alignment = ----
4416 std::min(Flags.getNonZeroByValAlign(), Align(RegSizeInBytes)); 0
4417 EVT PtrTy = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()), 0
4418 RegTy = MVT::getIntegerVT(RegSizeInBytes * 8); 0
4419 unsigned NumRegs = LastReg - FirstReg; 0
4420 ----
4421 if (NumRegs) { 0
4422 ArrayRef ArgRegs = ABI.GetByValArgRegs(); 0
4423 bool LeftoverBytes = (NumRegs * RegSizeInBytes > ByValSizeInBytes); 0
4424 unsigned I = 0; 0
4425 ----
4426 // Copy words to registers. ----
4427 for (; I < NumRegs - LeftoverBytes; ++I, OffsetInBytes += RegSizeInBytes) { 0
4428 SDValue LoadPtr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrTy, Arg, 0
4429 DAG.getConstant(OffsetInBytes, DL, PtrTy)); ----
4430 SDValue LoadVal = DAG.getLoad(RegTy, DL, Chain, LoadPtr, 0
4431 MachinePointerInfo(), Alignment); ----
4432 MemOpChains.push_back(LoadVal.getValue(1)); 0
4433 unsigned ArgReg = ArgRegs[FirstReg + I]; 0
4434 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(ArgReg, LoadVal)); 0
4435 } ----
4436 ----
4437 // Return if the struct has been fully copied. ----
4438 if (ByValSizeInBytes == OffsetInBytes) 0
4439 return; 0
4440 ----
4441 // Copy the remainder of the byval argument with sub-word loads and shifts. ----
4442 if (LeftoverBytes) { 0
4443 SDValue Val; 0
4444 ----
4445 for (unsigned LoadSizeInBytes = RegSizeInBytes / 2, TotalBytesLoaded = 0; 0
4446 OffsetInBytes < ByValSizeInBytes; LoadSizeInBytes /= 2) { 0
4447 unsigned RemainingSizeInBytes = ByValSizeInBytes - OffsetInBytes; 0
4448 ----
4449 if (RemainingSizeInBytes < LoadSizeInBytes) 0
4450 continue; 0
4451 ----
4452 // Load subword. ----
4453 SDValue LoadPtr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrTy, Arg, 0
4454 DAG.getConstant(OffsetInBytes, DL, ----
4455 PtrTy)); ----
4456 SDValue LoadVal = DAG.getExtLoad( 0
4457 ISD::ZEXTLOAD, DL, RegTy, Chain, LoadPtr, MachinePointerInfo(), ----
4458 MVT::getIntegerVT(LoadSizeInBytes * 8), Alignment); ----
4459 MemOpChains.push_back(LoadVal.getValue(1)); 0
4460 ----
4461 // Shift the loaded value. ----
4462 unsigned Shamt; ----
4463 ----
4464 if (isLittle) 0
4465 Shamt = TotalBytesLoaded * 8; 0
4466 else ----
4467 Shamt = (RegSizeInBytes - (TotalBytesLoaded + LoadSizeInBytes)) * 8; 0
4468 ----
4469 SDValue Shift = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, RegTy, LoadVal, 0
4470 DAG.getConstant(Shamt, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
4471 ----
4472 if (Val.getNode()) 0
4473 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, RegTy, Val, Shift); 0
4474 else ----
4475 Val = Shift; 0
4476 ----
4477 OffsetInBytes += LoadSizeInBytes; 0
4478 TotalBytesLoaded += LoadSizeInBytes; 0
4479 Alignment = std::min(Alignment, Align(LoadSizeInBytes)); 0
4480 } ----
4481 ----
4482 unsigned ArgReg = ArgRegs[FirstReg + I]; 0
4483 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(ArgReg, Val)); 0
4484 return; 0
4485 } ----
4486 } ----
4487 ----
4488 // Copy remainder of byval arg to it with memcpy. ----
4489 unsigned MemCpySize = ByValSizeInBytes - OffsetInBytes; 0
4490 SDValue Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrTy, Arg, 0
4491 DAG.getConstant(OffsetInBytes, DL, PtrTy)); ----
4492 SDValue Dst = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrTy, StackPtr, 0
4493 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(VA.getLocMemOffset(), DL)); 0
4494 Chain = DAG.getMemcpy( 0
4495 Chain, DL, Dst, Src, DAG.getConstant(MemCpySize, DL, PtrTy), ----
4496 Align(Alignment), /*isVolatile=*/false, /*AlwaysInline=*/false, ----
4497 /*isTailCall=*/false, MachinePointerInfo(), MachinePointerInfo()); ----
4498 MemOpChains.push_back(Chain); 0
4499 } ----
4500 ----
4501 void MipsTargetLowering::writeVarArgRegs(std::vector &OutChains, 0
4502 SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &DL, ----
4503 SelectionDAG &DAG, ----
4504 CCState &State) const { ----
4505 ArrayRef ArgRegs = ABI.GetVarArgRegs(); 0
4506 unsigned Idx = State.getFirstUnallocated(ArgRegs); 0
4507 unsigned RegSizeInBytes = Subtarget.getGPRSizeInBytes(); 0
4508 MVT RegTy = MVT::getIntegerVT(RegSizeInBytes * 8); 0
4509 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(RegTy); 0
4510 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction(); 0
4511 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo(); 0
4512 MipsFunctionInfo *MipsFI = MF.getInfo(); 0
4513 ----
4514 // Offset of the first variable argument from stack pointer. ----
4515 int VaArgOffset; ----
4516 ----
4517 if (ArgRegs.size() == Idx) 0
4518 VaArgOffset = alignTo(State.getStackSize(), RegSizeInBytes); 0
4519 else { ----
4520 VaArgOffset = 0
4521 (int)ABI.GetCalleeAllocdArgSizeInBytes(State.getCallingConv()) - 0
4522 (int)(RegSizeInBytes * (ArgRegs.size() - Idx)); 0
4523 } ----
4524 ----
4525 // Record the frame index of the first variable argument ----
4526 // which is a value necessary to VASTART. ----
4527 int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(RegSizeInBytes, VaArgOffset, true); 0
4528 MipsFI->setVarArgsFrameIndex(FI); 0
4529 ----
4530 // Copy the integer registers that have not been used for argument passing ----
4531 // to the argument register save area. For O32, the save area is allocated ----
4532 // in the caller's stack frame, while for N32/64, it is allocated in the ----
4533 // callee's stack frame. ----
4534 for (unsigned I = Idx; I < ArgRegs.size(); 0
4535 ++I, VaArgOffset += RegSizeInBytes) { 0
4536 unsigned Reg = addLiveIn(MF, ArgRegs[I], RC); 0
4537 SDValue ArgValue = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, Reg, RegTy); 0
4538 FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(RegSizeInBytes, VaArgOffset, true); 0
4539 SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0
4540 SDValue Store = ----
4541 DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, ArgValue, PtrOff, MachinePointerInfo()); 0
4542 cast(Store.getNode())->getMemOperand()->setValue( 0
4543 (Value *)nullptr); ----
4544 OutChains.push_back(Store); 0
4545 } ----
4546 } 0
4547 ----
4548 void MipsTargetLowering::HandleByVal(CCState *State, unsigned &Size, 0
4549 Align Alignment) const { ----
4550 const TargetFrameLowering *TFL = Subtarget.getFrameLowering(); 0
4551 ----
4552 assert(Size && "Byval argument's size shouldn't be 0."); 0
4553 ----
4554 Alignment = std::min(Alignment, TFL->getStackAlign()); 0
4555 ----
4556 unsigned FirstReg = 0; 0
4557 unsigned NumRegs = 0; 0
4558 ----
4559 if (State->getCallingConv() != CallingConv::Fast) { 0
4560 unsigned RegSizeInBytes = Subtarget.getGPRSizeInBytes(); 0
4561 ArrayRef IntArgRegs = ABI.GetByValArgRegs(); 0
4562 // FIXME: The O32 case actually describes no shadow registers. ----
4563 const MCPhysReg *ShadowRegs = ----
4564 ABI.IsO32() ? IntArgRegs.data() : Mips64DPRegs; 0
4565 ----
4566 // We used to check the size as well but we can't do that anymore since ----
4567 // CCState::HandleByVal() rounds up the size after calling this function. ----
4568 assert( 0
4569 Alignment >= Align(RegSizeInBytes) && ----
4570 "Byval argument's alignment should be a multiple of RegSizeInBytes."); ----
4571 ----
4572 FirstReg = State->getFirstUnallocated(IntArgRegs); 0
4573 ----
4574 // If Alignment > RegSizeInBytes, the first arg register must be even. ----
4575 // FIXME: This condition happens to do the right thing but it's not the ----
4576 // right way to test it. We want to check that the stack frame offset ----
4577 // of the register is aligned. ----
4578 if ((Alignment > RegSizeInBytes) && (FirstReg % 2)) { 0
4579 State->AllocateReg(IntArgRegs[FirstReg], ShadowRegs[FirstReg]); 0
4580 ++FirstReg; 0
4581 } ----
4582 ----
4583 // Mark the registers allocated. ----
4584 Size = alignTo(Size, RegSizeInBytes); 0
4585 for (unsigned I = FirstReg; Size > 0 && (I < IntArgRegs.size()); 0
4586 Size -= RegSizeInBytes, ++I, ++NumRegs) 0
4587 State->AllocateReg(IntArgRegs[I], ShadowRegs[I]); 0
4588 } ----
4589 ----
4590 State->addInRegsParamInfo(FirstReg, FirstReg + NumRegs); 0
4591 } 0
4592 ----
4593 MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitPseudoSELECT(MachineInstr &MI, 0
4594 MachineBasicBlock *BB, ----
4595 bool isFPCmp, ----
4596 unsigned Opc) const { ----
4597 assert(!(Subtarget.hasMips4() || Subtarget.hasMips32()) && 0
4598 "Subtarget already supports SELECT nodes with the use of" ----
4599 "conditional-move instructions."); ----
4600 ----
4601 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = ----
4602 Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
4603 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
4604 ----
4605 // To "insert" a SELECT instruction, we actually have to insert the ----
4606 // diamond control-flow pattern. The incoming instruction knows the ----
4607 // destination vreg to set, the condition code register to branch on, the ----
4608 // true/false values to select between, and a branch opcode to use. ----
4609 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock(); 0
4610 MachineFunction::iterator It = ++BB->getIterator(); 0
4611 ----
4612 // thisMBB: ----
4613 // ... ----
4614 // TrueVal = ... ----
4615 // setcc r1, r2, r3 ----
4616 // bNE r1, r0, copy1MBB ----
4617 // fallthrough --> copy0MBB ----
4618 MachineBasicBlock *thisMBB = BB; 0
4619 MachineFunction *F = BB->getParent(); 0
4620 MachineBasicBlock *copy0MBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
4621 MachineBasicBlock *sinkMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
4622 F->insert(It, copy0MBB); 0
4623 F->insert(It, sinkMBB); 0
4624 ----
4625 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to sinkMBB. ----
4626 sinkMBB->splice(sinkMBB->begin(), BB, 0
4627 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), BB->end()); ----
4628 sinkMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB); 0
4629 ----
4630 // Next, add the true and fallthrough blocks as its successors. ----
4631 BB->addSuccessor(copy0MBB); 0
4632 BB->addSuccessor(sinkMBB); 0
4633 ----
4634 if (isFPCmp) { 0
4635 // bc1[tf] cc, sinkMBB ----
4636 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Opc)) 0
4637 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
4638 .addMBB(sinkMBB); 0
4639 } else { ----
4640 // bne rs, $0, sinkMBB ----
4641 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Opc)) 0
4642 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
4643 .addReg(Mips::ZERO) 0
4644 .addMBB(sinkMBB); 0
4645 } ----
4646 ----
4647 // copy0MBB: ----
4648 // %FalseValue = ... ----
4649 // # fallthrough to sinkMBB ----
4650 BB = copy0MBB; 0
4651 ----
4652 // Update machine-CFG edges ----
4653 BB->addSuccessor(sinkMBB); 0
4654 ----
4655 // sinkMBB: ----
4656 // %Result = phi [ %TrueValue, thisMBB ], [ %FalseValue, copy0MBB ] ----
4657 // ... ----
4658 BB = sinkMBB; 0
4659 ----
4660 BuildMI(*BB, BB->begin(), DL, TII->get(Mips::PHI), MI.getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
4661 .addReg(MI.getOperand(2).getReg()) 0
4662 .addMBB(thisMBB) 0
4663 .addReg(MI.getOperand(3).getReg()) 0
4664 .addMBB(copy0MBB); 0
4665 ----
4666 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
4667 ----
4668 return BB; 0
4669 } 0
4670 ----
4671 MachineBasicBlock * ----
4672 MipsTargetLowering::emitPseudoD_SELECT(MachineInstr &MI, 0
4673 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
4674 assert(!(Subtarget.hasMips4() || Subtarget.hasMips32()) && 0
4675 "Subtarget already supports SELECT nodes with the use of" ----
4676 "conditional-move instructions."); ----
4677 ----
4678 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
4679 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
4680 ----
4681 // D_SELECT substitutes two SELECT nodes that goes one after another and ----
4682 // have the same condition operand. On machines which don't have ----
4683 // conditional-move instruction, it reduces unnecessary branch instructions ----
4684 // which are result of using two diamond patterns that are result of two ----
4685 // SELECT pseudo instructions. ----
4686 const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock(); 0
4687 MachineFunction::iterator It = ++BB->getIterator(); 0
4688 ----
4689 // thisMBB: ----
4690 // ... ----
4691 // TrueVal = ... ----
4692 // setcc r1, r2, r3 ----
4693 // bNE r1, r0, copy1MBB ----
4694 // fallthrough --> copy0MBB ----
4695 MachineBasicBlock *thisMBB = BB; 0
4696 MachineFunction *F = BB->getParent(); 0
4697 MachineBasicBlock *copy0MBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
4698 MachineBasicBlock *sinkMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB); 0
4699 F->insert(It, copy0MBB); 0
4700 F->insert(It, sinkMBB); 0
4701 ----
4702 // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to sinkMBB. ----
4703 sinkMBB->splice(sinkMBB->begin(), BB, 0
4704 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), BB->end()); ----
4705 sinkMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB); 0
4706 ----
4707 // Next, add the true and fallthrough blocks as its successors. ----
4708 BB->addSuccessor(copy0MBB); 0
4709 BB->addSuccessor(sinkMBB); 0
4710 ----
4711 // bne rs, $0, sinkMBB ----
4712 BuildMI(BB, DL, TII->get(Mips::BNE)) 0
4713 .addReg(MI.getOperand(2).getReg()) 0
4714 .addReg(Mips::ZERO) 0
4715 .addMBB(sinkMBB); 0
4716 ----
4717 // copy0MBB: ----
4718 // %FalseValue = ... ----
4719 // # fallthrough to sinkMBB ----
4720 BB = copy0MBB; 0
4721 ----
4722 // Update machine-CFG edges ----
4723 BB->addSuccessor(sinkMBB); 0
4724 ----
4725 // sinkMBB: ----
4726 // %Result = phi [ %TrueValue, thisMBB ], [ %FalseValue, copy0MBB ] ----
4727 // ... ----
4728 BB = sinkMBB; 0
4729 ----
4730 // Use two PHI nodes to select two reults ----
4731 BuildMI(*BB, BB->begin(), DL, TII->get(Mips::PHI), MI.getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
4732 .addReg(MI.getOperand(3).getReg()) 0
4733 .addMBB(thisMBB) 0
4734 .addReg(MI.getOperand(5).getReg()) 0
4735 .addMBB(copy0MBB); 0
4736 BuildMI(*BB, BB->begin(), DL, TII->get(Mips::PHI), MI.getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
4737 .addReg(MI.getOperand(4).getReg()) 0
4738 .addMBB(thisMBB) 0
4739 .addReg(MI.getOperand(6).getReg()) 0
4740 .addMBB(copy0MBB); 0
4741 ----
4742 MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now. 0
4743 ----
4744 return BB; 0
4745 } 0
4746 ----
4747 // FIXME? Maybe this could be a TableGen attribute on some registers and ----
4748 // this table could be generated automatically from RegInfo. ----
4749 Register ----
4750 MipsTargetLowering::getRegisterByName(const char *RegName, LLT VT, 0
4751 const MachineFunction &MF) const { ----
4752 // The Linux kernel uses $28 and sp. ----
4753 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit()) { 0
4754 Register Reg = StringSwitch(RegName) 0
4755 .Case("$28", Mips::GP_64) 0
4756 .Case("sp", Mips::SP_64) 0
4757 .Default(Register()); 0
4758 if (Reg) 0
4759 return Reg; 0
4760 } else { ----
4761 Register Reg = StringSwitch(RegName) 0
4762 .Case("$28", Mips::GP) 0
4763 .Case("sp", Mips::SP) 0
4764 .Default(Register()); 0
4765 if (Reg) 0
4766 return Reg; 0
4767 } ----
4768 report_fatal_error("Invalid register name global variable"); 0
4769 } ----
4770 ----
4771 MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitLDR_W(MachineInstr &MI, 0
4772 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
4773 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent(); 0
4774 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
4775 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
4776 const bool IsLittle = Subtarget.isLittle(); 0
4777 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
4778 ----
4779 Register Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
4780 Register Address = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
4781 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
4782 ----
4783 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I(MI); 0
4784 ----
4785 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r6() || Subtarget.hasMips64r6()) { 0
4786 // Mips release 6 can load from adress that is not naturally-aligned. ----
4787 Register Temp = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4788 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::LW)) 0
4789 .addDef(Temp) 0
4790 .addUse(Address) 0
4791 .addImm(Imm); 0
4792 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::FILL_W)).addDef(Dest).addUse(Temp); 0
4793 } else { ----
4794 // Mips release 5 needs to use instructions that can load from an unaligned ----
4795 // memory address. ----
4796 Register LoadHalf = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4797 Register LoadFull = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4798 Register Undef = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4799 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::IMPLICIT_DEF)).addDef(Undef); 0
4800 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::LWR)) 0
4801 .addDef(LoadHalf) 0
4802 .addUse(Address) 0
4803 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 0 : 3)) 0
4804 .addUse(Undef); 0
4805 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::LWL)) 0
4806 .addDef(LoadFull) 0
4807 .addUse(Address) 0
4808 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 3 : 0)) 0
4809 .addUse(LoadHalf); 0
4810 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::FILL_W)).addDef(Dest).addUse(LoadFull); 0
4811 } ----
4812 ----
4813 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
4814 return BB; 0
4815 } 0
4816 ----
4817 MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitLDR_D(MachineInstr &MI, 0
4818 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
4819 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent(); 0
4820 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
4821 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
4822 const bool IsLittle = Subtarget.isLittle(); 0
4823 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
4824 ----
4825 Register Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
4826 Register Address = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
4827 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
4828 ----
4829 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I(MI); 0
4830 ----
4831 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r6() || Subtarget.hasMips64r6()) { 0
4832 // Mips release 6 can load from adress that is not naturally-aligned. ----
4833 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit()) { 0
4834 Register Temp = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR64RegClass); 0
4835 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::LD)) 0
4836 .addDef(Temp) 0
4837 .addUse(Address) 0
4838 .addImm(Imm); 0
4839 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::FILL_D)).addDef(Dest).addUse(Temp); 0
4840 } else { ----
4841 Register Wtemp = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass); 0
4842 Register Lo = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4843 Register Hi = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4844 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::LW)) 0
4845 .addDef(Lo) 0
4846 .addUse(Address) 0
4847 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 0 : 4)); 0
4848 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::LW)) 0
4849 .addDef(Hi) 0
4850 .addUse(Address) 0
4851 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 4 : 0)); 0
4852 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::FILL_W)).addDef(Wtemp).addUse(Lo); 0
4853 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::INSERT_W), Dest) 0
4854 .addUse(Wtemp) 0
4855 .addUse(Hi) 0
4856 .addImm(1); 0
4857 } ----
4858 } else { ----
4859 // Mips release 5 needs to use instructions that can load from an unaligned ----
4860 // memory address. ----
4861 Register LoHalf = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4862 Register LoFull = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4863 Register LoUndef = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4864 Register HiHalf = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4865 Register HiFull = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4866 Register HiUndef = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4867 Register Wtemp = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass); 0
4868 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::IMPLICIT_DEF)).addDef(LoUndef); 0
4869 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::LWR)) 0
4870 .addDef(LoHalf) 0
4871 .addUse(Address) 0
4872 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 0 : 7)) 0
4873 .addUse(LoUndef); 0
4874 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::LWL)) 0
4875 .addDef(LoFull) 0
4876 .addUse(Address) 0
4877 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 3 : 4)) 0
4878 .addUse(LoHalf); 0
4879 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::IMPLICIT_DEF)).addDef(HiUndef); 0
4880 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::LWR)) 0
4881 .addDef(HiHalf) 0
4882 .addUse(Address) 0
4883 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 4 : 3)) 0
4884 .addUse(HiUndef); 0
4885 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::LWL)) 0
4886 .addDef(HiFull) 0
4887 .addUse(Address) 0
4888 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 7 : 0)) 0
4889 .addUse(HiHalf); 0
4890 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::FILL_W)).addDef(Wtemp).addUse(LoFull); 0
4891 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::INSERT_W), Dest) 0
4892 .addUse(Wtemp) 0
4893 .addUse(HiFull) 0
4894 .addImm(1); 0
4895 } ----
4896 ----
4897 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
4898 return BB; 0
4899 } 0

4901 MachineBasicBlock *MipsTargetLowering::emitSTR_W(MachineInstr &MI, 0
4902 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
4903 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent(); 0
4904 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
4905 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
4906 const bool IsLittle = Subtarget.isLittle(); 0
4907 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
4908 ----
4909 Register StoreVal = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
4910 Register Address = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0

4912 ----
4913 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I(MI); 0
4914 ----
4915 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r6() || Subtarget.hasMips64r6()) { 0
4916 // Mips release 6 can store to adress that is not naturally-aligned. ----
4917 Register BitcastW = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass); 0
4918 Register Tmp = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0

4922 .addUse(BitcastW) 0
4923 .addImm(0); 0

4925 .addUse(Tmp) 0
4926 .addUse(Address) 0
4927 .addImm(Imm); 0
4928 } else { ----
4929 // Mips release 5 needs to use instructions that can store to an unaligned ----
4930 // memory address. ----
4931 Register Tmp = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
4932 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY_S_W)) 0
4933 .addDef(Tmp) 0
4934 .addUse(StoreVal) 0
4935 .addImm(0); 0
4936 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::SWR)) 0
4937 .addUse(Tmp) 0
4938 .addUse(Address) 0
4939 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 0 : 3)); 0
4940 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::SWL)) 0
4941 .addUse(Tmp) 0
4942 .addUse(Address) 0
4943 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 3 : 0)); 0
4944 } ----
4945 ----
4946 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
4947 ----
4948 return BB; 0
4949 } 0

4952 MachineBasicBlock *BB) const { ----
4953 MachineFunction *MF = BB->getParent(); 0
4954 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
4955 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo(); 0
4956 const bool IsLittle = Subtarget.isLittle(); 0

4958 ----
4959 Register StoreVal = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
4960 Register Address = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
4961 unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
4962 ----
4963 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I(MI); 0
4964 ----
4965 if (Subtarget.hasMips32r6() || Subtarget.hasMips64r6()) { 0
4966 // Mips release 6 can store to adress that is not naturally-aligned. ----
4967 if (Subtarget.isGP64bit()) { 0
4968 Register BitcastD = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128DRegClass); 0
4969 Register Lo = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR64RegClass); 0
4970 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY)) 0
4971 .addDef(BitcastD) 0

4978 .addUse(Lo) 0

4986 .addDef(BitcastW) 0

4990 .addUse(BitcastW) 0
4991 .addImm(0); 0
4992 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY_S_W)) 0
4993 .addDef(Hi) 0
4994 .addUse(BitcastW) 0
4995 .addImm(1); 0
4996 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::SW)) 0
4997 .addUse(Lo) 0
4998 .addUse(Address) 0
4999 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 0 : 4)); 0
5000 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::SW)) 0
5001 .addUse(Hi) 0
5002 .addUse(Address) 0
5003 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 4 : 0)); 0
5004 } ----
5005 } else { ----
5006 // Mips release 5 needs to use instructions that can store to an unaligned ----
5007 // memory address. ----
5008 Register Bitcast = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::MSA128WRegClass); 0
5009 Register Lo = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
5010 Register Hi = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Mips::GPR32RegClass); 0
5011 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY)).addDef(Bitcast).addUse(StoreVal); 0
5012 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY_S_W)) 0
5013 .addDef(Lo) 0
5014 .addUse(Bitcast) 0
5015 .addImm(0); 0
5016 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::COPY_S_W)) 0
5017 .addDef(Hi) 0
5018 .addUse(Bitcast) 0
5019 .addImm(1); 0
5020 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::SWR)) 0
5021 .addUse(Lo) 0
5022 .addUse(Address) 0
5023 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 0 : 3)); 0
5024 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::SWL)) 0
5025 .addUse(Lo) 0
5026 .addUse(Address) 0
5027 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 3 : 0)); 0
5028 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::SWR)) 0
5029 .addUse(Hi) 0
5030 .addUse(Address) 0
5031 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 4 : 7)); 0
5032 BuildMI(*BB, I, DL, TII->get(Mips::SWL)) 0
5033 .addUse(Hi) 0
5034 .addUse(Address) 0
5035 .addImm(Imm + (IsLittle ? 7 : 4)); 0
5036 } ----
5037 ----
5038 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
5039 return BB; 0
